&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;0 0 []&quot; style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;KPFK is celebrating 60 years on the air!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;0 0 []&quot;&gt;Key Note Speaker &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Amy Goodman&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of Democracy Now!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hosted by &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Richard Montoya&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of Culture Clash&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Celebrity Auctioneer -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Jack Black&lt;/strong&gt;, Actor, Musician, and Two-Time Golden Globe Nominee Musical&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Performances By:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Legendary producer and musician&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Don Was&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;will lead an all-star band including David Bowie&amp;#39;s longtime pianist&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Mike Garson&lt;/strong&gt;, original founding members of&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The Doors&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;John Densmore &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;Robby&amp;nbsp;Krieger&lt;/strong&gt;, bassist extraordinaire&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Stanley Clarke&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;The Haden Triplets&lt;/strong&gt;, and many more surprise musical guests!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Guests Include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sonali Kolhatkar,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;host of &amp;quot;Rising Up&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ian Masters&lt;/strong&gt;, host of &amp;quot;Background Briefing&amp;quot;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Jimmy Dore,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;host of the &amp;quot;Jimmy Dore Show&amp;quot;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Stephanie Miller&lt;/strong&gt;, host of the &amp;quot;Stephanie Miller Show&amp;quot;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Freya Rojo&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;host of&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Nuestra Voz&amp;quot;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Pamela Anchang&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;founder of &amp;quot;The Immigrant Magazine&amp;quot;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lisa Garr&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;host of &amp;quot;The Aware Show&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:20px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Honoring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blase Bonpane&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;former host of &amp;quot;World Focus&amp;quot; -&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Antonio Gonzalez &lt;/strong&gt;former&amp;nbsp;host of &amp;quot;Strategy Session&amp;quot; -&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Calibri&amp;quot;,sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Doran Barons&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;former host of &amp;quot;Digital Village&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;-&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Roy of Hollywood&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of &amp;quot;Something&amp;rsquo;s Happening&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Uncle Ruthie&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;of &amp;quot;Half Way Down the Stairs&amp;quot; and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lila Garret&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;of &amp;quot;Connect the Dots&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;KPFK was the second of five stations in the non-commercial Pacifica Foundation network. The Pacifica Foundation was founded in the late 1940s out of the peace movement surrounding World War II, becoming the birthplace of a listener-sponsored radio.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;KPFK has been broadcasting since 1959 over 110,000 - Watts, the strongest signal west of the Mississippi. KPFK continues to produce the majority of programs in-house giving it the flexibility to provide a platform for stories, news, music, and information to serve the cultural welfare of the communities in and around Southern California that you will not hear anywhere else. KPFK believes forging social change is a fundamental part of how radio can make a positive impact on communities.&lt;/p&gt;

