    &lt;div class=&quot;show-history&quot;&gt;
        &lt;h2 class=&quot;section-header&quot;&gt;History &amp; Legacy&lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Since 1987, Kathy Díaz has anchored Latin music programming at KPFK, notably as co-host of &quot;Canto Tropical&quot; and through her longstanding commitment to Global Village’s Monday edition. Over decades, her broadcasts have amplified Los Angeles’ vibrant Latino arts and elevated local artists seldom heard on commercial radio. With an extensive collection of vinyl and CDs, Kathy has maintained an authentic sound rooted in community and culture. Her ongoing work as a board member for Empowering Latino Futures and advocate with the International Latino Book Awards further underscores her dedication to uplifting Latino voices and heritage across the airwaves.&lt;/p&gt;
