See the trailer here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Oe1jrYFHyzE&quot; style=&quot;color:blue; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Oe1jrYFHyzE&lt;/a&gt; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: Every Rembrandt exhibition is eagerly anticipated but this major show hosted by London&amp;rsquo;s National Gallery and Amsterdam&amp;rsquo;s Rijksmuseum was an event like no other. &amp;nbsp;Given privileged access to both galleries, Rembrandt documents this landmark exhibition while interweaving the artist&amp;#39;s life story with behind-the-scenes preparations at these world famous institutions. Exploring many of the exhibition&amp;rsquo;s key works, through contributions from specially invited guests including curators and leading art historians, this EXHIBITION ON SCREEN favorite makes a welcome return to the big screen. &amp;nbsp;For many, Rembrandt is the greatest artist who ever lived and this deeply moving film seeks to explore the truth about the man behind the legend.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Calibri&amp;quot;,sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:uppercase&quot;&gt;That Part Feeling - The Universe of Arvo Part&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;Screens Monday, 5/27, 7:30PM, and Tuesday, 5/28 1 PM, at the most fabulous Laemmle Playhouse 7, Royal, Town Center 5, and Claremont 5 Theaters.&lt;br /&gt;
Part of the Laemmle Culture Vulture series. For more info visit the film&amp;rsquo;s webpage: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://drupal-stage.laemmle.com/film/part-feeling-universe-arvo-part&quot; style=&quot;color:blue; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;https://drupal-stage.laemmle.com/film/part-feeling-universe-arvo-part&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;AND call 818-985-2711 to request an available complimentary pair of tickets, if you are a Film Club Member, or to JOIN the KPFK Film Club and ENJOY THE FUN!!!&lt;br /&gt;
See the trailer here: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R2VB-ic1Ssc&quot; style=&quot;color:blue; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R2VB-ic1Ssc&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Arvo P&amp;auml;rt is is the most performed living composer in the world, but he is considered to be something of a recluse, and his person and work have rarely been documented on film. In this documentary we get to know Arvo P&amp;auml;rt as an artist combining an incredible sensitivity with humor and energy in his work. His reputation stems from his deeply-held belief that it&amp;rsquo;s not through words that a great artist communicates, but simply through music. Though he may seem reclusive in his person, what he wants to say and what he means is written in notes. &amp;nbsp;P&amp;auml;rt is known for his minimalistic style that employs his self-invented compositional technique &amp;quot;tintinnabuli.&amp;quot; It is this harmonious, spiritual and minimalistic approach to music that forms the basis of That P&amp;auml;rt Feeling &amp;ndash; a feeling of wholeness, beauty and essence of being, embraced by millions of persons all around the world. P&amp;auml;rt&amp;rsquo;s intense collaboration with the Cello Octet Amsterdam is at the heart of this documentary, which sheds a bright light on P&amp;auml;rt&amp;rsquo;s universe. A universe not only inhabited by classical musicians like T&amp;otilde;nu Kaljuste, Candida Thompson or Daniel Reuss, but also by choreographers like Jiř&amp;iacute; Kyli&amp;aacute;n, filmmakers like Alain Gomis and young musicians like Kara-Lis Coverdale. They are all looking for &amp;quot;that P&amp;auml;rt feeling.&amp;quot; &amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;Arvo P&amp;auml;rt&amp;rsquo;s music is a house on fire and an infinite calm.&amp;quot; Michael Stipe. &amp;nbsp; &amp;quot;He gives space to the listeners; he can go inside the music and live there.&amp;quot; Bj&amp;ouml;rk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:uppercase&quot;&gt;Klimt &amp;amp; Schiele: Eros &amp;amp; Psyche&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:107%&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;Screens Monday, 5/20, 7:30PM, and Tuesday, 5/21 1 PM, at the most fabulous Laemmle Playhouse 7, Royal, Town Center 5, and Claremont 5 Theaters.&lt;br /&gt;
Part of the Laemmle Culture Vulture series. For more info visit the film&amp;rsquo;s webpage: &lt;a href=&quot;https://drupal-stage.laemmle.com/index.php/film/klimt-schiele-eros-psyche&quot; style=&quot;color:blue; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;https://drupal-stage.laemmle.com/index.php/film/klimt-schiele-eros-psyche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
AND call 818-985-2711 to request an available complimentary pair of tickets, if you are a Film Club Member, or to JOIN the KPFK Film Club and ENJOY THE FUN!!!&lt;br /&gt;
See the trailer here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Td7jpg1wq-4&quot; style=&quot;color:blue; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Td7jpg1wq-4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Klimt &amp;amp; Schiele: Eros and Psyche, recounts the start of the Vienna Secession, a magical art movement formed in the late 1890&amp;#39;s for art, literature and music, in which new ideas are circulated, Freud discovers the drives of the psyche, and women begin to claim their independence. It was a movement that marked a new era outside the confines of academic tradition. &amp;nbsp;At the heart of Secession were artists Gustav Klimt and his prot&amp;eacute;g&amp;eacute; and dear friend Egon Schiele. This exhibition proves an in-depth examination of images of extraordinary visual power: from the eroticism of Klimt&amp;#39;s mosaic-like works, to the anguished and raw work of the young Schiele in his magnetic nudes and contorted figures against the backdrop of nocturnal Vienna, full of masked balls and dreams imbued with sexuality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

