See the trailer here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://vimeo.com/323308357&quot; style=&quot;color:blue; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;https://vimeo.com/323308357&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: If the Dancer Dances invites viewers into the intimate world of the dance studio. Stephen Petronio, one of today&amp;rsquo;s leading dance-makers, is determined to help his dancers breathe new life into RainForest (1968), an iconic work by the legendary choreographer Merce Cunningham. &amp;nbsp;With help from three members of the former Cunningham company, the film tracks Petronio&amp;rsquo;s dancers as they strive to re-stage this great work, revealing what it takes to keep a dance &amp;ndash; and a legacy &amp;ndash; alive. Timed to coincide with Cunningham&amp;rsquo;s centennial, If the Dancer Dances is the first documentary on the subject of Cunningham&amp;rsquo;s work since his passing in 2009.&amp;ldquo;The dance studio is a private and mysterious place. After all, it&amp;rsquo;s where great works of choreography are created and kept alive. If the Dancer Dances grants us rare access, bringing us into the studio to watch the staging of a Merce Cunningham masterwork on the Stephen Petronio Company. It&amp;rsquo;s the tracking of this intimate process, a dance being passed one body to another, that makes this film a great gift.&amp;rdquo; - Mikhail Baryshnikov. &amp;#39;If the Dancer Dances&amp;#39; grants us rare access [to an] intimate process, a dance being passed one body to another, that makes this film a great gift.&amp;rdquo; --Mikhail Baryshnikov&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Calibri&amp;quot;,sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:uppercase&quot;&gt;Nureyev&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
