&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;On Saturday, April 27th, legendary Wurlitzer whiz Dean Mora lends Live Musical Accompaniment to Buster Keaton&amp;rsquo;s silent 1928 comedy classic Steamboat Bill, Jr.! &amp;nbsp;When college boy William Canfield Jr. (Keaton) reunites with his boat captain father in a Mississippi River town, the elder Canfield seems to have found an ally to help him compete with fellow riverboat owner John James King &amp;ndash; despite the fact that he&amp;rsquo;s a bit flummoxed by Willie&amp;rsquo;s citified nature. Soon Willie finds himself falling for King&amp;rsquo;s daughter, Mary (Marion Byron) &amp;ndash; but he has more pressing concerns when the weather turns bad&amp;hellip;This one-time-only event is presented by Orange County film collective Flickrhappy! &amp;nbsp;Experience Keaton&amp;rsquo;s 91-year-old classic on the big screen, with a new soundtrack performed live by a silent-film musical legend!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

