&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Join Frida Cinema Lovers April 27th as the Bombs Away Show&amp;mdash;the podcast that loves to tear apart the Best of the Worst&amp;mdash;returns to take on &amp;ldquo;The Epitome of So-Bad-It&amp;rsquo;s-Good Cinema,&amp;rdquo; Plan 9 from Outer Space! &amp;nbsp;You&amp;rsquo;ve seen Tim Burton&amp;rsquo;s Ed Wood (Screening at The Frida Cinema April 22nd and 23rd), you&amp;rsquo;ve heard the name&amp;mdash;now experience Plan 9 From Outer Space in a special 60th anniversary screening with a live comedy podcast following the film. First, sit back and enjoy the cult classic that combines aliens, zombies, and Bela Legosi in his final role in a film that critics have stated &amp;ldquo;has become so famous for its own badness that it&amp;rsquo;s now beyond criticism.&amp;rdquo; &amp;nbsp;But one podcast is gonna try! Because with this screening, you also get to enjoy a live recording of Bombs Away! The B-Movie comedy podcast will bring its show to you with special guests live on stage to dissect the movie you just experienced and invite you to participate with an audience discussion during the show! &amp;ndash; Step into a themed event that transports you to the Black-and-White campy world of ED WOOD and 1950s B-Movie Madness featuring iconic trailers, themed drinks, and cheesy decor. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; Pose with in a green screen set recreation of Plan 9! &amp;nbsp;Tickets include both the film and the post-screening podcast show! Get in line early, tickets will sell out&amp;mdash;you will not want to miss out on this one-night-only event!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

