Get more info at the Frida&amp;rsquo;s website: &amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://thefridacinema.org/event/creature-from-the-black-lagoon-and-book-signing/?instance_id=6862&quot; style=&quot;color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline&quot;&gt;http://thefridacinema.org/event/creature-from-the-black-lagoon-and-book-signing/?instance_id=6862&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Join The Frida Cinema for a special screening of 1954 classic The Creature from the Black Lagoon &amp;ndash; followed by a Discussion &amp;amp; Book Signing with author Mallory O&amp;rsquo;Meary, and her new novel The Lady from the Black Lagoon: Hollywood Monsters and the Lost Legacy of Milicent Patrick! The Lady from the Black Lagoon: Hollywood Monsters and the Lost Legacy of Milicent Patrick uncovers the life and work of Milicent Patrick, was one of Disney&amp;rsquo;s first female animators, and in creating the film&amp;rsquo;s iconic creature, is the only woman in history to create one of Hollywood&amp;rsquo;s classic movie monsters! Author Mallory O&amp;rsquo;Meary will detail her true-life detective work in recognizing the brilliance of Milicent Patrick&amp;rsquo;s work, and a celebration of a forgotten feminist trailblazer.&amp;nbsp; Mallory O&amp;rsquo;Meara&amp;rsquo;s The Lady from the Black Lagoon: Hollywood Monsters and the Lost Legacy of Milicent Patrick establishes Patrick in her rightful place in film history &amp;ndash; while calling out a Hollywood culture where little has changed since.&amp;nbsp; This event is FREE, and first-come, first-served! Enjoy a night of classic horror and contemporary literature!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

