&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Directed by Iranian filmmaker Asghar Farhadi, and starring Javier Bardem and Pen&amp;eacute;lope Cruz, EVERYBODY KNOWS is an exciting psychological thriller. &amp;nbsp;Laura, on her travels from Argentina to her small home town in Spain for her sister&amp;rsquo;s wedding, brings her two children along for the occasion. Amid the joyful reunion and festivities, the eldest daughter is abducted. In the tense days that follow, various family and community tensions surface and deeply hidden secrets are revealed. &amp;ldquo;A quietly gripping examination of societal divisions, of class, of secrets that bind us together and pull us apart.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; The Wrap. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;If this were a book, it would be described as a page-turner.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Arizona Republic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

