&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: With over five million copies of her Neapolitan Novels sold and publication rights in 50 countries, Elena Ferrante is a global literary sensation. A journey between New York City&amp;rsquo;s cultural hub and Ferrante&amp;rsquo;s native Italy explores how an anonymous, translated author&amp;rsquo;s visceral tales of love and friendship gained such an enthusiastic following. Ann Goldstein, Sarah McNally, Jonathan Franzen and others weigh in on the Ferrante &amp;ldquo;craze&amp;rdquo; and what makes her work -- and her mysterious persona -- so uniquely captivating.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

