&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;One of the GREATEST FILMS of ALL TIME&amp;hellip;On Thursday, February 21st, join The Frida Cinema as they celebrate their 5th Anniversary with a special screening of 1942&amp;rsquo;s Casablanca! Ticket holders are welcome to join The Frida at 6:30pm for a pre-screening mixer, with hors d&amp;rsquo;oeuvres and drinks included with your ticket! &amp;nbsp;At 7:30pm, enjoy a brief presentation where The Frida will highlight their non-profit art house cinema&amp;rsquo;s accomplishments over their first Five Years, as well as some of their visions for the future! Then sit back and experience a 4K Restoration of one of the greatest films of all time &amp;ndash; director Michael Curtiz&amp;rsquo; Casablanca! &amp;nbsp;Far more than a simple period romance, Casablanca is an inspiring epic that showcases humanity at its best in the face of impending political doom. &amp;nbsp;In World War II Casablanca, Rick Blaine (Humphrey Bogart), exiled American and former freedom fighter, runs the most popular nightspot in town, having given up The Fight to run a den of gambling, extortion, and excess. As a Nazi presence grows in Casablanca, a twist of fate finds Rick in possession of two valuable letters of transit &amp;ndash; which can mean an escape from Nazi persecution for Czechoslovakian underground leader Victor Laszlo, who arrives in Casablanca for those very letters. There&amp;rsquo;s only one problem &amp;ndash; Lazslo arrives with his wife Ilsa, who is Rick&amp;rsquo;s one-time love, and chief cause of his newfound heartache and hardened cynicism&amp;hellip;Tickets include pre-screening hors d&amp;rsquo;oeuvres and drinks, as well as popcorn and soft drinks for the show! &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

