&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: Cold War is a passionate love story between a man and a woman who meet in the ruins of post-war Poland. With vastly different backgrounds and temperaments, they are fatefully mismatched and yet condemned to each other. Set against the background of the Cold War in 1950s Poland, Berlin, Yugoslavia and Paris, it&amp;rsquo;s the tale of a couple separated by politics, character flaws and unfortunate twists of fate &amp;ndash; an impossible love story in impossible times. &amp;ldquo;Cold War resembles a waking dream. And a ravishingly romantic one at that.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; &amp;nbsp;Entertainment Weekly. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;A film that is both illuminating and haunting at the same time.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Observer. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;One of the most colourful things you&amp;rsquo;ll ever see in black and white.&amp;rdquo; &amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; Time Out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

