&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;Director Neil Burger&amp;rsquo;s THE UPSIDE is a heartfelt comedy about a recently paroled ex-convict, Dell (Kevin Hart), who strikes up an unusual and unlikely friendship with a quadriplegic billionaire, Phillip Lacasse (Bryan Cranston). From worlds apart, Dell and Phillip form an unlikely bond, bridging their differences and gaining invaluable wisdom in the process, giving each man a renewed sense of passion for all of life&amp;rsquo;s possibilities. THE UPSIDE also stars Nicole Kidman, Julianna Margulies, and Aja Naomi King. &amp;nbsp;The screenplay for the film is by Jon Hartmere, based on the motion picture Intouchables by &amp;Eacute;ric Toledano and Olivier Nakache.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

