&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: Laemmle Theaters&amp;rsquo; Culture Vulture Series presents&amp;hellip;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:uppercase&quot;&gt;The Madness of George III&lt;/span&gt;. Multi-award-winning drama &lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:uppercase&quot;&gt;The Madness of George III&lt;/span&gt; captured live at the Nottingham Playhouse. Written by one of Britain&amp;rsquo;s best-loved playwrights Alan Bennett (The History Boys, The Lady in the Van), this epic play was also adapted into a BAFTA Award-winning film following its premiere on stage in 1991. The cast of this new production includes Olivier Award-winners Mark Gatiss (Sherlock, Wolf Hall, NT Live Coriolanus) in the title role, and Adrian Scarborough (Gavin and Stacey, Upstairs Downstairs, After the Dance). It&amp;rsquo;s 1786 and King George III is the most powerful man in the world. But his behavior is becoming increasingly erratic as he succumbs to fits of lunacy. With the King&amp;rsquo;s mind unraveling at a dramatic pace, ambitious politicians and the scheming Prince of Wales threaten to undermine the power of the Crown, and expose the fine line between a King and a man.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;margin-bottom:11px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:uppercase&quot;&gt;Genesis 2.0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
