In Disney&amp;rsquo;s MARY POPPINS RETURNS an all new original musical and sequel, Mary Poppins is back to help the next generation of the Banks family find the joy and wonder missing in their lives following a personal loss. Emily Blunt stars as the practically-perfect nanny with unique magical skills who can turn any ordinary task into an unforgettable, fantastic adventure and Lin-Manuel Miranda plays her friend Jack, an optimistic street lamplighter who helps bring light&amp;mdash;and life&amp;mdash;to the streets of London. &amp;nbsp;MARY POPPINS RETURNS is directed by Rob Marshall and features a wonderful screen story by Magee &amp;amp; Rob Marshall &amp;amp; John DeLuca based upon the Mary Poppins Stories by PL Travers. You&amp;rsquo;ll love the all new original songs and music by Marc Shaiman with lyrics by Scott Wittman and Shaiman. &amp;nbsp;MARY POPPINS RETURNS also stars Ben Whishaw as Michael Banks; Emily Mortimer as Jane Banks; Julie Walters as the Banks&amp;rsquo; housekeeper Ellen; Pixie Davies, Nathanael Saleh and introducing Joel Dawson as the Banks&amp;rsquo; children, with Colin Firth as Fidelity Fiduciary Bank&amp;rsquo;s William Weatherall Wilkins; and Meryl Streep as Mary&amp;rsquo;s eccentric cousin, Topsy. Angela Lansbury appears as the Balloon Lady, a treasured character from the PL Travers books and Dick Van Dyke is Mr. Dawes, Jr., the retired chairman of the bank now run by Firth&amp;rsquo;s character.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

