&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;In 1967, The Beatles embarked on an ambitious project, writing and directing a one-hour film, Magical Mystery Tour. The music written for the film is some of The Beatles&amp;rsquo; psychedelic best. &amp;nbsp;In &amp;ldquo;Deconstructing The Beatles&amp;rsquo; Magical Mystery Tour&amp;rdquo;, music historian, composter and Beatles enthusiast Scott Freiman delves into the creative process behind &amp;ldquo;The Fool On The Hill,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Blue Jay Way,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;I Am The Walrus,&amp;rdquo; and other selections from Magical Mystery Tour. &amp;nbsp;Scott will also &amp;ldquo;deconstruct&amp;rdquo; other songs from the Magical Mystery Tour album, including &amp;ldquo;Strawberry Fields Forever,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Penny Lane,&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;All You Need Is Love.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

