&lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt; The ART Theater in Long Beach Proudly Presents&amp;hellip;.ROMA--The Most Personal Project to date from Academy Award (R)-winning Director and Writer Alfonso Cuar&amp;oacute;n!! &amp;nbsp;ROMA follows Cleo, a young domestic worker for a family in the middle-class neighborhood of Roma in Mexico City. Delivering an artful love letter to the women who raised him, Cuar&amp;oacute;n draws on his own childhood to create a vivid and emotional portrait of domestic strife and social hierarchy amidst political turmoil of the 1970s. New York Film Critics have named &amp;lsquo;Roma&amp;rsquo; the Best Film of 2018! &amp;ldquo;Cuar&amp;oacute;n has composed some of the most stunning shots and sequences in film history, and it would be a sin not to see this on the big screen.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; L.A. Weekly. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;It&amp;rsquo;s an expansive, emotional portrait of life buffeted by violent forces, and a masterpiece.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; New York Times. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;A richly textured masterpiece, Roma is cinema at its purest and most human.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Time Out&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

