&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: La Sylphide, Captured Live from the Bolshoi Ballet in Moscow! A Fabulous Laemmle Theaters&amp;rsquo; Culture Vulture Feature!!! The ultimate romantic masterpiece and the first ballet choreographed entirely on pointe, LA SYLPHIDE follows the winged creature from Scotland&amp;#39;s enchanted forests who appears in dreams. On his wedding day, the young Scotsman James is awakened with a kiss from an ethereal winged creature, a Sylph. Entranced by her beauty, James risks everything to pursue an unattainable love. La Sylphide is one of the world&amp;rsquo;s oldest surviving ballets, and a treasure in Danish ballet master August Bournonville&amp;rsquo;s style. Staged for the Bolshoi by Bournonville expert Johan Kobborg, this production is the ultimate romantic masterpiece.You&amp;#39;ll entranced by the beauty of the Sylph.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

