&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;MARIA BY CALLAS: IN HER OWN WORDS is an intimate look at the life and work of Greek-American opera singer, Maria Callas, one of the most renowned and influential opera singers of the 20th century, as told in her own words. Told through performances, TV interviews, home movies, family photographs, private letters and unpublished memoirs&amp;mdash;nearly all of which have never been shown to the public&amp;mdash;the film reveals the essence of an extraordinary woman who rose from humble beginnings in New York City to become a glamorous international superstar and one of the greatest artists of all time. Assembling the material for the film took director Tom Volf four years of painstaking research, which included personal outreach to dozens of Callas&amp;rsquo;s closest friends and associates, who allowed him to share their personal memorabilia in the film. When recordings of Callas&amp;rsquo;s voice aren&amp;rsquo;t available, Joyce DiDonato, one of contemporary opera&amp;rsquo;s biggest stars, reads her words.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

