&lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt; &amp;nbsp;A new production of one of the funniest plays in English, Oscar Wilde&amp;rsquo;s The Importance of Being Earnest, will be captured live at the Vaudeville Theatre in London&amp;rsquo;s West End. Wilde&amp;rsquo;s much-loved masterpiece throws love, logic and language into the air to make one of theatre&amp;rsquo;s most dazzling firework displays. &amp;nbsp;Jack, Algy, Gwendolyn and Cecily discover how unsmooth runs the course of true love, while Lady Bracknell keeps a baleful eye on the mayhem of manners. &amp;nbsp;Michael Fentiman&amp;rsquo;s witty new production stars Olivier Award winner Sophie Thompson (Guys and Dolls, Chichester/West End; Four Weddings and a Funeral) and Jeremy Swift (Downton Abbey, ITV), alongside Fiona Button (The Split, BBC), Pippa Nixon (A Midsummer Night&amp;rsquo;s Dream, RSC) and Stella Gonet (Handbagged, Hampstead Theatre/West End). &amp;nbsp;A fresh take on Wilde&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;comic masterpiece&amp;rsquo; (Guardian), this &amp;lsquo;hilarious&amp;rsquo; adaptation breaths &amp;lsquo;new and vital&amp;rsquo; life (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Segoe UI Symbol&amp;quot;,sans-serif&quot;&gt;★★★★★&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt; WhatsOnStage) into &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&amp;lsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;one of the most immaculately crafted stage comedies of all time&amp;rsquo; (The Stage). Don&amp;rsquo;t miss the &amp;lsquo;magnificent&amp;rsquo; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Segoe UI Symbol&amp;quot;,sans-serif&quot;&gt;★★★★&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt; Sunday Times) final instalment of Classic Spring&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;,serif&quot;&gt;s critically acclaimed Oscar Wilde Season, a year-long celebration of the brilliant Victorian playwright.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

