&lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt; &amp;nbsp;THE HAPPY PRINCE&amp;hellip;A Portrait of the Dark Side of a Genius Who Lived and Died for Love. Starring Rupert Everett, Colin Firth, Emily Watson, Colin Morgan, Edwin Thomas, Tom Wilkinson. &amp;nbsp;Best known for his epigrams and plays, Oscar Wilde was a turn-of-the-century Irish poet and playwright whose Gothic novel The Picture of Dorian Gray and satirical play The Importance of Being Earnest are still popular today. Once one of the most famous men in London, Oscar Wilde was crucified by a society that once worshipped him--a lover, imprisoned and freed. &amp;nbsp;The HAPPY PRINCE stars Rupert Everett who, capturing the author&amp;rsquo;s brilliant wit and flamboyant style, gives a career defining performance as Wilde, physically and emotionally embodying the literary genius as he lives out his last days in exile in Europe. The critics are effusive: &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Moving, unforgettable, ravishing, a gutsy tour deforce&amp;rdquo; &amp;nbsp;-Metro; &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Rupert Everett is an exceptional Oscar Wilde&amp;rdquo;-Screen Daily; &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Rupert Everett is MAGNIFICENT!&amp;rdquo;-The Guardian.&amp;nbsp; THE HAPPY PRINCE opens in New York and Los Angeles October 10th but YOU can be one of the first to see it early by calling in now!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

