&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: &amp;nbsp;From director Panos Cosmatos (Beyond the Black Rainbow) and RLJ Entertainment comes highly-anticipated action-thriller Mandy, starring &amp;nbsp;Nicolas Cage and Andrea Riseborough! &amp;nbsp; The Frida&amp;rsquo;s one-week run kicks off with a special 8pm screening on Thursday the 13th which will be followed by a pre-taped (note: NOT LIVE or in-person!) Q&amp;amp;A with Nicolas Cage and director Panos Cosmatos, recorded at L.A.&amp;rsquo;s legendary Egyptian Theatre!!** &amp;nbsp;Pacific Northwest, 1983 AD. Outsiders Red Miller and Mandy Bloom lead a loving and peaceful existence. When their pine-scented haven is savagely destroyed by a cult led by the sadistic Jeremiah Sand, Red is catapulted into a phantasmagorical journey filled with bloody vengeance, and laced with fire. To delve deeper into Mandy here would be to risk spoiling many of the film&amp;rsquo;s surprises &amp;ndash; or as Heather Wixson of Daily Dead wrote in her five-star review, &amp;ldquo;There are so many reasons why I loved Mandy, and I feel like I&amp;rsquo;ve barely scratched the surface here &amp;ndash; but to be honest, so many of those things were genuine surprises for me as I was watching it, and I feel like that&amp;rsquo;s the best way for anyone to see it.&amp;rdquo; &amp;nbsp;Directed by Panos Cosmatos. 2018. 121 minutes. Rated R. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Were scientists to engineer an uncut, 100-proof cult sensation, it would probably look, sound, and kick like this.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; A.A. Dowd, AV Club; &amp;ldquo;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;Segoe UI Symbol&amp;quot;,sans-serif&quot;&gt;★★★★&lt;/span&gt;. Those still suffering from withdrawal symptoms from the end of David Lynch&amp;rsquo;s epic Twin Peaks revival last year &amp;ndash; the cure has been found.&amp;rdquo;&amp;ndash; James Croot, Stuff.co.nz; &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Mandy is a totally uncompromising vision from a singular filmmaker &amp;ndash; a pulsing, twisted descent into heavy metal vengeance that must be seen to be believed.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Ben Pearson, Slashfilm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

