&lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt; The Laemmle Theaters Culture Vulture Series Presents: &amp;nbsp;Egon Schiele: Death and the Maiden. &amp;nbsp;At the beginning of the 20th century, Egon Schiele was one of the most provocative artists in Vienna. His erotic paintings scandalized Viennese society while art agents and daring artists like his mentor Gustav Klimt truly understood the exceptionality of his work. Now, almost 100 years after Schiele&amp;rsquo;s tragic death in 1918, this dramatic film celebrates this fascinating artist with wonderful cinematography and casting which bring to life the biographical story of an artist prepared to go beyond his own pain to sacrifice love and life for his art. Winner of numerous international awards!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

