Description: Kino Lorber presents a New 4k Restoration of the Landmark Labor Movement Documentary, and a 2021 Library of Congress National Film Registry Inductee! &amp;ldquo;A vivid look into America&amp;rsquo;s radical past.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Pulitzer Prize Winner, Studs Terkel. &amp;nbsp;The Wobblies premiered at the 1979 New York Film Festival and tells the story of the radical labor union, the Industrial Workers of the World or IWW, better known as the Wobblies, which championed the formation of &amp;ldquo;one big union&amp;rdquo; for all unskilled laborers, regardless of their race and gender. This story is brought to life through a combination of rare archival footage, period artwork, and songs including many written by Joe Hill, complemented by illuminating interviews with surviving Union members.&lt;/p&gt;

