Description: &amp;nbsp;Film Movement Classics presents a New 2K Restoration of Ang Lee&amp;#39;s highly Acclaimed Debut! &amp;nbsp;Having just moved from Beijing, elderly tai chi master Mr. Chu (Sihung Lung) struggles to adjust to life in New York, living with his Americanized son Alex (Ye-tong Wang). Chu immediately butts heads with his put-upon white daughter-in-law, Martha (Deb Snyder), a writer who seems to blame him for her own paralyzing inability to focus. But when Chu begins teaching tai chi at a local school, his desire to make a meaningful connection comes to fruition in the most unexpected of ways. PUSHING HANDS is the debut film from Oscar-winning director Ang Lee (CROUCHING TIGER, HIDDEN DRAGON and BROKEBACK MOUNTAIN.)&lt;/p&gt;

