Description: Strand Releasing presents a loving Film By Oren Gerner. &amp;nbsp;Nominated for 5 Ophir Awards including Best Picture and winner of 3 Haifa International Film Festival Awards including Best Film, Best Debut Film and Best Actor, the touching and heartwarming film AFRICA finds 68-year-old Meir discovering that his 30 years of planning the annual village celebration have been summarily discarded and the job has been given to inexperienced local teens instead. In his effort to restore a sense of meaning and vitality, Meir begins to rebel against the inevitable: the betrayal of his physical body, the growing distance from his children, and the loss of relevance. Reconstructing fiction from real life, AFRICA is the cinematic journey of an ageing parent crafted by the hands of his loving son, in this deeply personal story on reinventing oneself. &amp;nbsp;Official Selection at the Toronto International Film Festival.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FROM CHANGLINGS TO WITCHES, FOLKLORE COMES TO THE BIG SCREEN THIS SPRING!&lt;br /&gt;
Two Exciting Thrillers Coming&amp;hellip;Soon&amp;hellip;your way!!!&lt;br /&gt;
YOU ARE NOT MY MOTHER, March 25 via Magnolia. &amp;nbsp;It&amp;rsquo;s the week before Halloween and Char&amp;rsquo;s mother, Angela, has inexplicably disappeared. All that remains is her abandoned car. When she returns home without explanation the following evening, it becomes clear to Char and her grandmother, Rita, that something is amiss. She might look and sound the same but Angela&amp;rsquo;s behavior has become increasingly frightening, as if she has been replaced by a malevolent force. When Halloween arrives, a night steeped in ancient myth and legend, Char realizes that she is the only one who can save her, even if it means potentially losing her forever.&lt;br /&gt;
More info here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://magnetreleasing.com/youarenotmymother/&quot;&gt;http://magnetreleasing.com/youarenotmymother/&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;; enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AoNbm72YLqA&amp;amp;t=2s&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AoNbm72YLqA&amp;amp;t=2s&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3150103298598208&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/&lt;wbr /&gt;permalink.php?story_fbid=&lt;wbr /&gt;3150103298598208&amp;amp;id=&lt;wbr /&gt;1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
YOU WON&amp;#39;T BE ALONE, April 1 via Focus Features.&amp;nbsp; Set in an isolated mountain village in 19th century Macedonia, YOU WON&amp;rsquo;T BE ALONE follows a young girl who is kidnapped and then transformed into a witch by an ancient spirit. Curious about life as a human, the young witch accidentally kills a peasant in the nearby village and then takes her victim&amp;rsquo;s shape to live life in her skin. Her curiosity ignited, she continues to wield this horrific power in order to understand what it means to be human. &amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3151191271822744&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3151191271822744&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;More info here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.focusfeatures.com/you-wont-be-alone&quot;&gt;https://www.focusfeatures.com/you-wont-be-alone&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;; enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6-G39n2sCVU&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6-G39n2sCVU&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

