Description: IFC FILMS is proud to present the riveting new thriller from two-time Academy Award-nominee Hany Abu-Assad! Based on real events, HUDA&amp;rsquo;S SALON is a timely political drama about two women who find themselves in a dangerous and complex web of betrayal. &amp;nbsp;Nadia, a young mother married to a jealous man, goes to Huda&amp;#39;s salon in Bethlehem. But this ordinary visit turns sour when Huda, after having put Nadia in a shameful situation, blackmails her to have her work for the secret service of the occupiers, and thus betray her people. Written and directed by Hany Abu-Assad (PARADISE NOW, OMAR, THE IDOL), starring Ali Suliman (TOM CLANCY&amp;#39;S JACK RYAN, PARADISE NOW), Maisa Abd Elhadi (BAGHDAD CENTRAL) and Manal Awad (GAZA MON AMOUR).&lt;/p&gt;

