Description: The Los Angeles Jewish Film Festival presents a SPECIAL VALENTINE&amp;#39;S DAY PROGRAM! An aging screen legend (Mariette Hartley) and jobless voiceover actor (Jerry Sroka) navigate the LA senior dating scene, in this (mostly) true-life romantic dramedy. Who would expect anything to come from two people who first meet in a bird store? She&amp;rsquo;s tall, famous and classy. He&amp;rsquo;s short and hides behind Groucho Marx and Woody Allen impressions. &amp;nbsp;Out-of-work actors of a certain age face the indignities of Gen Z Hollywood assistants, oblivious to names, and agents who ignore calls. Despite their baggage, early life traumas and a serious health crisis, as these opposites attract, they find it&amp;rsquo;s never too late for love. Set against the beautiful backdrop of Los Angeles, this adorable crowd-pleaser is also a love letter to Hollywood. &amp;nbsp;Directed by Emmy winner Don Scardino (30 Rock), starring MARIETTE HARTLEY, JERRY SROKA, MORGAN FAIRCHILD, TESS HARPER, BERNIE KOPELL, and PETER MCNICHOL&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;THE NEED TO GROW&amp;hellip;A documentary that centers around the urgent issue of topsoil depletion.&lt;br /&gt;
For just a few days, you can watch this award-winning documentary for free; click here for info and access:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://grow.foodrevolution.org/?orid=3162651&amp;amp;opid=314&amp;amp;mc_cid=d897317132&amp;amp;mc_eid=10ba287cb0&quot;&gt;https://grow.foodrevolution.org/?orid=3162651&amp;amp;opid=314&amp;amp;mc_cid=d897317132&amp;amp;mc_eid=10ba287cb0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Get more info here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.earthconsciouslife.org/theneedtogrow&quot;&gt;https://www.earthconsciouslife.org/theneedtogrow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0pBYu4U525Y&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0pBYu4U525Y&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: &amp;ldquo;If we take care of Mother Nature, Mother Nature takes care of us.&amp;rdquo; A deeply moving 90-minute documentary &amp;mdash; the kind that gives you chills, opens your heart, and leaves you informed about some of the most critical issues of our times. The focus of this film is on soil, food, and the future of our species &amp;mdash; told through the lens of three extraordinary and very likable characters and their journeys as solutionaries: Alicia Serratos&amp;mdash;An 8-year-old girl challenges the ethics of a global organization. Erik Cutter&amp;mdash;A renegade farmer struggles to keep his land as he revolutionizes resource-efficient agriculture. Michael Smith&amp;mdash;A visionary inventor faces catastrophe in the midst of developing a game-changing technology.&amp;nbsp;THE NEED TO GROW&amp;nbsp;is narrated by top-notch celebrity activist Rosario Dawson and brings a non-divisive message about the stake we all have in humanity&amp;rsquo;s ability to sustainably grow food for future generations. Fantastic Fungi director, Louie Schwartzberg was a mentor to the film&amp;#39;s director, Rob Herring.&lt;/p&gt;

