Description: At the beginning of 1979, after more than 30 years of collective repression, a dramatized and emotional US television miniseries brought the horrors of Nazi crimes into German living rooms and ensured that the German population was suddenly reminded of the heinous crimes against the Jews. What is now expressed with the unknown word &amp;lsquo;Holocaust&amp;rsquo;, hits many millions of people in the heart. This was the first time that a major mainstream drama had portrayed the lives of Hitler&amp;rsquo;s victims.&lt;/p&gt;

