Description: &amp;ldquo;A two-lane - virtual and physical - rebel highway of radical &amp;lsquo;cinema-sations&amp;rsquo; that are guaranteed to not just entertain, but to challenge the mind and shock the senses!&amp;rdquo; The third edition of Film Maudit 2.0, a showcase and celebration of new (and some old) outr&amp;eacute;, unusual and startling films takes places January 12-23, 2022 at the legendary L.A. Performance Space and Gallery Highways. &amp;nbsp;This year, Film Maudit 2.0 features over 100 genre, experimental, animated and documentary works of cinema from 23 countries including films rarely if ever, seen in festivals: works addressing socio-political issues and taboo subject matter that challenges conventional artistic assumptions and sexual mores. encompassing genre, experimental, animated and documentary works. &amp;nbsp;The hybrid festival will present both live screenings @ Highways, as well virtual, online screenings of 12 feature films, 10 shorts programs, specially commissioned sections, and a collection of new scores to silent films starring the iconic Lon Chaney by artists who reflect the diversity of Los Angeles. &amp;nbsp;Included in the festival are a range of narrative, documentary and experimental films that are deliberately bold, extreme, confrontational and unusual. &amp;nbsp;Film Maudit 2.0 is inspired by French avant-garde filmmaker and writer Jean Cocteau who created the original Festival du Film Maudit (literally &amp;ldquo;cursed films&amp;rdquo;) in 1949 aiming to celebrate overlooked, shocking and experimental films. &amp;nbsp;Feature Films making L.A. premieres, Shorts Programs BEHOLD! Queer Film + Performance Series (&lt;a href=&quot;https://filmmaudit.eventive.org/films?mode=list&amp;amp;filterTags%5B61cd28c7abe18a0044411d13%5D=true&quot;&gt;https://filmmaudit.eventive.org/films?mode=list&amp;amp;filterTags%5B61cd28c7abe18a0044411d13%5D=true&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;), and much, much, more!&lt;/p&gt;

