Description: A charming political documentary. &amp;nbsp;After decades of quiet living, 89-year-old former U.S. senator Mike Gravel comes out of retirement when a group of teenagers convince him to run for president. Through Senator Gravel&amp;#39;s official Twitter account, the Gravel teens embark on an unlikely adventure to qualify him for the Democratic debates in order to advance an anti-war, anti-corruption, and direct democracy agenda in the 2020 presidential race. &amp;nbsp;Directed by Skye Wallin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BOB SPIT &amp;ndash; WE DO NOT LIKE PEOPLE (Bob Cuspe &amp;ndash; N&amp;oacute;s N&amp;atilde;o Gostamos de Gente)&lt;br /&gt;
Get more info at the Outsider website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.outsiderpictures.us/&quot;&gt;https://www.outsiderpictures.us/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u9KUZF6m84A&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u9KUZF6m84A&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3078341155774423&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/&lt;wbr /&gt;permalink.php?story_fbid=&lt;wbr /&gt;3078341155774423&amp;amp;id=&lt;wbr /&gt;1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
The Stop Motion Animation/Documentary/ Comedy/Road Movie Based on the Classic Comic Strips of&lt;br /&gt;
Legendary Brazilian Cartoonist Angeli opens on Wednesday, December 15 at the Laemmle NoHo 7 in Los Angeles (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.laemmle.com/film/bob-spit-we-do-not-people&quot;&gt;https://www.laemmle.com/film/bob-spit-we-do-not-people&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;)&lt;br /&gt;
Description: &amp;nbsp;Outsider Pictures is proud to announce the U.S. theatrical release. Bob Spit: We Do Not Like People tells the story of Bob Spit, an old punk trying to escape from a post-apocalyptic desert that is actually, a purgatory inside the mind of his creator, Angeli, a cartoonist going through a creative crisis. The story is freely inspired by the life and work of one of the most celebrated Brazilian cartoonists of all times, Angeli, who became famous in the seventies by releasing political cartoons in the midst of Brazil&amp;rsquo;s military dictatorship. &amp;nbsp;In the eighties, he migrated to daily strips, showing an acid sense of humor to represent Brazil&amp;rsquo;s society, day-to-day life and customs. Angeli had editorial success with his monthly magazine &amp;ldquo;Chiclete com Banana&amp;rdquo;, which sold over 120 thousand copies per edition. During his time, the cartoonist has created some of his most famous characters: the bohemian diva Rê Bordosa, the hippie pair Wood &amp;amp; Stock, and the punk Bob Spit. &amp;quot;One of the year&amp;rsquo;s zaniest and best-received indie animated features&amp;quot;&amp;mdash;Cartoon Brew. Winner of Top Awards at the Annecy and Ottawa Animation Film Festivals.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

