Description: &amp;nbsp;A documentary from Hong Kong by Kiwi Chow.&amp;nbsp; Over the past fifty years, Hongkongers have fought for freedom and democracy but have yet to succeed. In 2019, the &amp;ldquo;Extradition Bill&amp;rdquo; to China opened a Pandora&amp;rsquo;s box, turning Hong Kong into a battlefield against the Chinese authoritarian rule. &amp;nbsp;The award-winning director of &amp;ldquo;Ten Years: Self Immolator,&amp;rdquo; Kiwi Chow, made this documentary to tell the story of the movement both with a macro view of its historical context and up close and personal on the front lines. The film covers seven teams of protestors with different stories which are put together as a comprehensive picture of the versatile movement. The film was the Official Selection at the 2021 Cannes Film Festival, and it won the Best Documentary Award at the 2021 Golden Horse Festival in Taiwan.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MISSING IN BROOKS COUNTY&lt;br /&gt;
Now streaming on all Video on Demand sites.&lt;br /&gt;
Get more info and enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.missinginbrookscounty.com/&quot;&gt;https://www.missinginbrookscounty.com/&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3072709396337599&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3072709396337599&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: &amp;quot;A sobering piece of film about frustration with our nation&amp;rsquo;s systemic inhumanity&amp;quot;- Film International. &amp;nbsp;Tackling the true struggles of life at the border, MISSING IN BROOKS COUNTY takes an unflinching look at the realities facing migrants and the life-and-death consequences of our broken immigration system. This must-see documentary puts a human face on a political issue and showcases the complications of illegal border crossings. &amp;nbsp;Two families arrive in Brooks County, Texas to look for their loved ones who went missing after crossing into the country from Mexico. On their search they meet vigilante ranchers, human smugglers, humanitarian activists, and Border Patrol agents, all of whom are locked in a proxy version of the national immigration debate. They also discover a sobering truth: the deadliest part of the journey was far from the border. A gripping investigative documentary, Missing in Brooks County is a portrait of a place that confronts the life-and-death consequences of a broken immigration system. Directed by Lisa Molomot and Jeff Bemiss; Main Cast includes Eduardo Canales, Omar Roman &amp;amp; Michelle Roman, Moises Zavala, Dr. Kate Spradley, Dr. Mike Vickers.&lt;/p&gt;

