Description: Coming soon from strand releasing! &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;A gentle reflection on memory and death, featuring Constance Wu as the ghost of a woman who returns to comfort her Japanese Hawaiian husband near the end of his life.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; The Hollywood Reporter. &amp;nbsp;I WAS A SIMPLE MAN is a ghost story set in the pastoral countryside of the north shore of O&amp;lsquo;ahu, Hawai&amp;lsquo;i. Revealed in four chapters, the film tells the story of an elderly man facing the end of his life, visited by the ghosts of his past. Incorporating familial history and mythology, dream logic and surrealism, I Was a Simple Man is a time-shifting, kaleidoscopic story of a fractured family facing the death of their patriarch that will take us from the high-rises of contemporary Honolulu to pre-WWII pastorals of O&amp;lsquo;ahu and, finally, into the beyond.&lt;/p&gt;

