Description: The ARPA International Film Festival is proud to present a world premiere! For the first time, the extraordinary&amp;nbsp;THE AMERICAN GOOD SAMARITANS&amp;nbsp;reveals the untold story of how thousands of fearless and compassionate, ordinary Americans helped refugees and survivors of the Armenian Genocide believe in a better future. &amp;nbsp;This is a story about survivors; extraordinary people who saved Christian lives from total destruction. American writers, genocide scholars and survivors, and other independent researchers reveal the details related to the genocides of Armenian, Assyrian and Greek populations, carried out by the Ottoman Empire (today&amp;rsquo;s Turkey). After the first two screenings,&amp;nbsp;GRACE AND GRIT, a film by Sebastian Siegel, will be screened, based on a true story of the iconic philosopher Ken Wilber and his wife, Treya.&lt;/p&gt;

