Description: the latest work from madman-genius filmmaker Paul Verhoeven. &amp;nbsp;A 17th-century nun in Italy suffers from disturbing religious and erotic visions. She is assisted by a companion, and the relationship between the two women develops into a romantic love affair. An IFC Films Release, BENEDETTA stars Virginie Efira (SIBYL) as Benedetta, a historical figure whose extraordinary story was captured in Judith C. Brown&amp;rsquo;s book Immodest Acts: The Life of a Lesbian Nun in Renaissance Italy. &amp;nbsp;Efira&amp;rsquo;s powerhouse performance masterfully tows the line between saint and sinner - is she a power-hungry fraud or the true vessel of God? &amp;nbsp;The film features veterans Charlotte Rampling and Lambert Wilson, and a radiant Daphne Patakia co-stars as Bartolomea, the object of Benedetta&amp;rsquo;s desire. BENEDETTA ignited a flurry of buzz around its premiere at this year&amp;rsquo;s Cannes Film Festival.&lt;/p&gt;

