Description: German Currents has become a mainstay of Los Angeles&amp;rsquo; cultural calendar and a highlight for film-goers throughout Southern California. Celebrating its 15th edition this year, the festival takes place in the American Cinematheque theaters in Los Feliz and Santa Monica and at the brand-new Goethe-Institut space in the MacArthur Park neighborhood, as a hybrid event including special in-person and virtual cinema screenings. The return of audiences to theaters is a reminder of the power the cinema has to bring people together. This idea of the cinema as a space for community, dialogue, and exchange is at the heart of German Currents&amp;rsquo; goal to present the best of current German films to a broad and diverse audience.&lt;br /&gt;
October 24, 11:00am, Goethe-Institut L.A., Sarah Winkenstette,&amp;nbsp;TOO FAR AWAY)--This multi-award-winning children&amp;rsquo;s film is a touching coming-of-age story for the whole family that masterfully combines entertainment, emotion, and meaningful storytelling. Free in-person Kindermatinee! Also streaming virtually in the U.S. through October 31&lt;br /&gt;
October 24, 5:00pm, Aero Theater, Dominik Graf,&amp;nbsp;FABIAN:&amp;nbsp;GOING TO THE DOGS--Dominik Graf&amp;rsquo;s dazzling adaptation of Erich K&amp;auml;stner&amp;rsquo;s classic novel takes viewers into the underbelly of Weimar Berlin. Winner of three German Film Awards. With Saskia Rosendahl and Tom Schilling (Never Look Away). West Coast premiere. There are still some tickets left for this free in-person screening!&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3133139523627919&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3133139523627919&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
