Description: &amp;nbsp;thrilling drama from Kino Lorber&amp;hellip;A hardworking Maltese fisherman (Jesmark) is faced with an agonizing choice. &amp;nbsp;He can repair his leaky luzzu &amp;ndash; a traditional, multicolored wooden fishing boat &amp;ndash; in the hopes of eking out a meager living at sea for his wife and newborn son, just as his father and grandfather did before him. Or he can decommission it in exchange for an EU payout and cast his lot with a sinister black-market operation that is decimating the Mediterranean fish population and the livelihoods of the local families who depend on it. Directed by breakthrough Maltese-American filmmaker, Alex Camilleri, starring Jesmark Scicluna &amp;amp; Michela Farrugia. &amp;nbsp;LUZZU won a Sundance Jury Prize for its nonprofessional lead actor, a real-life Maltese fisherman.&lt;/p&gt;

