Description: &amp;nbsp;Winner, Best Director at the Jerusalem Film Festival! How did a man in charge of 12 million slave laborers become &amp;ldquo;the good Nazi&amp;rdquo;? &amp;nbsp;SPEER GOES TO HOLLYWOOD offers an intriguing look at the inner workings of a man responsible for the deaths of millions, yet whom many people still consider a decent man in indecent circumstances. This new film by director Vanessa Lapa, award-winning director of The Decent One (2014), is a cautionary tale about Albert Speer&amp;rsquo;s 1971 attempt to whitewash his past with a Hollywood adaptation of his bestselling wartime memoir, &amp;quot;Inside the Third Reich&amp;rdquo;. &amp;nbsp;A Realworks LTD theatrical release. A documentary film by Vanessa Lapa.&lt;/p&gt;

