Enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://youtu.be/OdBvO2LJ1qE&quot;&gt;https://youtu.be/OdBvO2LJ1qE&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3054699971471875&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3054699971471875&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: &amp;nbsp;Blerta Basholli&amp;rsquo;s HIVE is Kosovo&amp;rsquo;s Official OscarⓇ&amp;nbsp;Entry for Best International Feature Film!!! &amp;nbsp;HIVE is a searing drama based on the true story of Fahrije (Yllka Gashi), who, like many of the other women in her patriarchal village, has lived with fading hope and burgeoning grief since her husband went missing during the war in Kosovo. In order to provide for her struggling family, she pulls together the other widows in her community to launch a business selling a local food product. Finding healing and solace in considering a future without their husbands&amp;mdash;but their will to begin living independently is met with hostility. The men in the village condemn Fahrije&amp;rsquo;s efforts to empower herself and the women around her, starting a feud that threatens their newfound sovereignty&amp;mdash;and the financial future of Fahrije&amp;rsquo;s family. Against the backdrop of Eastern Europe&amp;rsquo;s civil unrest and lingering misogyny, Fahrije and the women of her village join in a struggle to find hope in the face of an uncertain future. HIVE is a pithy, devastating portrait of loss and our uphill journeys to freedom. &amp;quot;An engrossing, utterly classic tale of overcoming adversity &amp;quot;- Deborah Young, THE HOLLYWOOD REPORTER&lt;/p&gt;

