Description: Explosive action thriller selected as the centerpiece film for the New York Asian Film Festival! Featuring a powerhouse cast headlined by international martial arts action superstar Donnie Yen (Mulan, Ip Man franchise) and Nicholas Tse (Shaolin, New Police Story), RAGING FIRE is the last film of the late Hong Kong director Benny Chan (NEW POLICE STORY, THE WHITE STORM, BIG BULLET), renowned for his award-winning action films. &amp;nbsp;Shan (Donnie Yen) is a highly respected hardline cop with a long history of success on dangerous cases. However, his past unexpectedly comes back to haunt him when a sting operation is attacked by a mysterious group of criminals led by Ngo (Nicholas Tse), his former prot&amp;eacute;g&amp;eacute;, a talented former officer who had once respected and admired Shan. However, a terrible mistake three years prior landed him in prison, quickly turning the once rising star into a furious man with a grudge, and the will to destroy everyone who had wronged him&amp;mdash;including his former mentor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HOLA M&amp;Eacute;XICO FILM FESTIVAL,&amp;nbsp;Presented by DishLATINO, Returns for Its 13th Annual Edition&lt;br /&gt;
September 17-25 during Hispanic Heritage Month&lt;br /&gt;
In-person screenings (7:00 pm ) will take place at Regal Cinemas LA Live, located at 1000 W Olympic Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90015&lt;br /&gt;
Opening (9/17) &amp;amp; Closing (9/21) ceremonies will take place at LA Plaza de Cultura Y Artes (an open-air venue), 501 N Main St, Los Angeles, CA 90012&lt;br /&gt;
For tickets, passes, and information, please visit:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.holamexicoff.com/&quot;&gt;www.holamexicoff.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: Bringing audiences back to the cinema, Hola M&amp;eacute;xico Film Festival, the largest Mexican film festival outside of the Mexican territory, will give viewers an opportunity to gather once again to celebrate the perseverance of the film community and see some of the most compelling films that have recently come out of Mexico. The Hola M&amp;eacute;xico Film Festival will feature 21 films, kicking off with Perdida from revered Mexican director Jorge Michel Grau (&amp;ldquo;We Are What We Are&amp;rdquo;) a sleek thriller, of marital intrigue and deceit. &amp;nbsp;Perdida trailer here: https://youtu.be/hUSWtsiNnnQ. The Hola M&amp;eacute;xico Film Festival is comprised of the following sections: &amp;nbsp;M&amp;eacute;xico Ahora, Documental, El Otro M&amp;eacute;xico, and Nocturno. M&amp;eacute;xico Ahora features the best of Mexican films released in recent years, covering every genre. Documental includes notable non-fiction films made by Mexican filmmakers. El Otro Mexico highlights experiences of Mexicans rarely portrayed on screen, skillfully presenting perceptive narratives that challenge the status quo. The Nocturno section offers offbeat stories and horror films. The Hola M&amp;eacute;xico Festival is also proud to reveal this year&amp;rsquo;s key art by the Mexico City-based Lourdes Villagomez. &amp;nbsp;The festival will conclude with an award ceremony; recognitions will include best director, best short film, and best audience award.As public health measures from the County of Los Angeles are rapidly changing, information on social distancing and/or mask requirements will be clarified closer to event date.&lt;/p&gt;

