Description: Well Go USA presents an exciting thriller, based on a true story. &amp;nbsp;Two years before the events of BLACK HAWK DOWN, Korean diplomats trapped in war-torn Somalia attempt a daring ESCAPE FROM MOGADISHU. As civil war rages in Mogadishu, rival North and South Korean diplomats are left trapped. With no aid from either government, their only shot at survival may require uniting with bitter adversaries to escape. &amp;nbsp;Directed by directed by Ryoo Seung-wan, ESCAPE FROM MOGADISHU stars Kim Yoon-seok (The Chaser, The Yellow Sea), Huh Joon-ho (Kingdom, Illang: The Wolf Brigade), Zo In-sung (The Classic, The Great Battle), Koo Kyo-hwan (Train to Busan Presents: Peninsula, Netflix&amp;rsquo;s Kingdom: Ashin of the North), Joung Man-sik [Jeong Man-sik] (The Swordsman, Rampant), and Kim So-jin (The Spy Gone North, The King.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DATING &amp;amp; NEW YORK&lt;br /&gt;
Opens in select theaters and everywhere films are rented digitally, Friday, Sept. 10th;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3007169816224891&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/&lt;wbr /&gt;permalink.php?story_fbid=&lt;wbr /&gt;3007169816224891&amp;amp;id=&lt;wbr /&gt;1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: A NEW ROMANTIC COMEDY FROM IFC FILMS! &amp;nbsp;Wendy (Francesca Reale) and Milo (Jaboukie Young-White), both jaded about their love lives, are thrown together at what might be the worst, most complicated time for romance in their lives. &amp;nbsp;In spite of their reluctance, the magic of New York and a few profound text messages just might be the transformative force they need to find love. &amp;nbsp;Their L-Train fueled-quest for love ultimately begs the question: can &amp;#39;happily ever after&amp;#39; truly exist in the age of read receipts? &amp;nbsp;The classic romantic comedy gets a millennial update, complete with fast-paced dialogue, a cast of up-and-coming comedians, and perpetual affection for one of the most romantic cities in the world. &amp;nbsp;DATING &amp;amp; NEW YORK features a stand-out cast, including JABOUKIE YOUNG-WHITE (The Daily Show), FRANCESCA REALE (Stranger Things), CATHERINE COHEN (Search Party), BRIAN MULLER (Bridge and Tunnel), JERRY FERRARA (Entourage)&lt;/p&gt;

