Enjoy the trailers here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://youtu.be/tRgJdq0_EzY&quot;&gt;https://youtu.be/tRgJdq0_EzY&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://youtu.be/V2hnf-n_aRU&quot;&gt;https://youtu.be/V2hnf-n_aRU&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp; ;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2987575438184329&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2987575438184329&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;LITTLE Q--Little Q, a yellow lab with a curious birthmark, is training to become a guide dog for the blind. &amp;nbsp;When his training is complete, Little Q is sent to help Lee Bo Ting, a famous, recently blinded chef. &amp;nbsp;Irritable and bitter, Bo Ting is at first reluctant to rely on Little Q and even tries to drive him away several times. &amp;nbsp;But through his loyalty, Little Q eventually teaches Bo Ting how to trust again, opening him up to a new life of wonderful possibilities. Award-winning actor Simon Yam (IP Man) stars in this family-friendly drama, and leads a cast that also includes Gigi Leung (The Monkey King 3), Him Law (The Monkey King 2), Charlie Yeung (Bangkok Dangerous), Shanshan Yuan (Lobster Cop), Angela Yeun (The White Girl), Frankie Lam (The Merger), and Roger Kwok (Kung Fu Mahjong).&lt;br /&gt;
MIDNIGHT DINER--A small, counter-only restaurant, open daily from midnight to 7, is lovingly helmed by its mysterious owner and chef, a quiet enigma who provides no menu yet can make any dish the customer desires. &amp;nbsp;Year after year, people flock from far and wide to the mysterious Midnight Diner to share their stories, savor delicious home cooking, and finally, to leave refreshed, feeling equally full and ready for their next adventure. This delightful comedy-drama and is based on the celebrated manga series &amp;ldquo;Shin&amp;rsquo;ya Shokudo&amp;rdquo; by Yaro Abe and previously adapted into the critically-acclaimed TV series in Japan, Korea and China. Tony Leung Ka-Fai (Once Upon a Time in Hong Kong) makes his directorial debut and plays the leading role in a cast that also stars Deng Chao (Shadow), Eddie Peng (Operation Mekong), and Vision Wei (Lost in White).&lt;/p&gt;

