Description: Strand releasing presents an Official Selection of the Berlin International Film Festival! Few true stories tread the thin line between good and evil as precariously as that of Jan Mikol&amp;aacute;&amp;scaron;ek, a 20th century Czech herbal healer whose great success masked the grimmest of secrets. Mikol&amp;aacute;&amp;scaron;ek won fame and fortune treating celebrities of the interwar, Nazi, and Communist eras with his uncanny knack for &amp;ldquo;urinary diagnosis&amp;rdquo;. &amp;nbsp;But his passion for healing welled up from the same source as a lust for cruelty, sadism, and an incapacity for love that only one person could ever quell &amp;ndash; his assistant, Franti&amp;scaron;ek. &amp;nbsp;As a show trial threatens to pry open these secrets and undo him, Jan&amp;rsquo;s dichotomies are put to a final test, with the fate of his life&amp;rsquo;s only love in the balance. A personal tale as replete with twists as the century itself, and a reflection on the price one pays for single-mindedly following one&amp;rsquo;s calling. Czech Republic&amp;#39;s official entry to the 93rd Academy Awards for Best International Film. A Film By Agniezska Holland, legendary Academy Award Nominated filmmaker of iconic films Europa Europa, In Darkness, Angry Harvest, and Spoor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FIRST DATE&lt;br /&gt;
Hits the theaters, including the Laemmle Theaters (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.laemmle.com/film/first-date&quot;&gt;https://www.laemmle.com/film/first-date&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;), and VOD on July 2.&lt;br /&gt;
More info available at the film&amp;rsquo;s website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.magnetreleasing.com/firstdate/&quot;&gt;http://www.magnetreleasing.com/firstdate/&lt;/a&gt;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2954971548111385&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2954971548111385&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: A ZANY ACTION COMEDY FROM MAGNOLIA&amp;#39;S MAGNET RELEASING. In this out-all-night throwback thrill ride from first time directing duo Manuel Crosby and Darren Knapp, shy, wide-eyed high schooler Mike finally summons the courage to ask out his badass neighbor Kelsey, only to realize he&amp;rsquo;s missing a key element for a successful date - the car. Panicked and low on cash, he&amp;rsquo;s conned into buying a beat-up &amp;lsquo;65 Chrysler. &amp;nbsp;Mike&amp;#39;s plan to win over Kelsey soon turns into a surreal misadventure when they are inexplicably targeted by a pair of cops, a criminal gang, and a vengeful cat lady. A night fueled by desire, bullets, and burning rubber makes any other first date seem like a walk in the park. FIRST DATE weaves together elements of dark comedy, teen romance, shoot &amp;#39;em up action and classic coming-of-age story, creating a truly entertaining ride that never misses a beat. This refreshing mix of tones, coupled with a break-out performance from Tyson Brown as Mike, make FIRST DATE a truly outstanding first feature. FIRST DATE was a Sundance favorite and has been compared to &amp;quot;Superbad meets True Romance&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CAN YOU BRING IT: BILL T. JONES AND D-MAN IN THE WATERS&lt;br /&gt;
Opens in select theaters and virtual cinemas on Friday, July 16th, &amp;nbsp;at Film Forum in New York, &amp;nbsp;and on Friday, July 23rd at Laemmle&amp;#39;s Royal in Los Angeles (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.laemmle.com/film/can-you-bring-it-bill-t-jones-and-d-man-waters&quot;&gt;https://www.laemmle.com/film/can-you-bring-it-bill-t-jones-and-d-man-waters&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;), with national rollout to follow.&lt;br /&gt;
More info can be had at the Kino Lorber website: &amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kinolorber.com/film/view/id/4821&quot;&gt;https://www.kinolorber.com/film/view/id/4821&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zvdqTFNCUwc&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zvdqTFNCUwc&lt;/a&gt;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2969314500010423&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/&lt;wbr /&gt;permalink.php?story_fbid=&lt;wbr /&gt;2969314500010423&amp;amp;id=&lt;wbr /&gt;1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: Kino Lorber is proud to present&amp;hellip;CAN YOU BRING IT: BILL T. JONES AND D-MAN IN THE WATERS brings to life the creative process that culminated in choreographer-dancer-director Bill T. Jones&amp;rsquo;s tour de force ballet D-Man in the Waters, one of the most important works of art to come out of the AIDS crisis. In 1989, D-Man in the Waters gave physical manifestation to the fear, anger, grief, and hope for salvation that the emerging Bill T. Jones/Arnie Zane Company (both partners at the time) felt as they were embattled by the AIDS epidemic. As a group of young dancers in the present re-interpret the work, they deepen their understanding of its power &amp;ndash; exploring what is at stake in their own personal lives in order to commit and perform it successfully. Through an extraordinary collage of interviews, archival material, and uniquely powerful cinematography, this lyrical documentary uses the story of this iconic dance to illustrate the power of art and the triumph of the human spirit.&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2969314500010423&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/&lt;wbr /&gt;permalink.php?story_fbid=&lt;wbr /&gt;2969314500010423&amp;amp;id=&lt;wbr /&gt;1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;JOHN AND THE HOLE&lt;br /&gt;
Opens Friday, August 6, 2021, In Select Theatres and Everywhere Films Are Rented&lt;br /&gt;
More info available at the IFC website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ifcfilms.com/films/john-and-the-hole&quot;&gt;https://www.ifcfilms.com/films/john-and-the-hole&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2979273132347893&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;br /&gt;
Description: IFC FILMS PRESENTS A psychological coming-of-age thriller. In this enigmatic and unsettling meditation on adolescent angst, 13-year-old John (Charlie Shotwell) discovers an unfinished bunker while exploring the neighboring woods&amp;mdash;a deep hole in the ground. Seemingly without provocation, he drugs his affluent parents (Michael C. Hall and Jennifer Ehle) and older sister (Taissa Farmiga), holding them captive within the bunker. &amp;nbsp;As they anxiously wait for John to free them from the hole, the boy returns home, where he can finally enjoy and explore a newfound independence. &amp;ldquo;Remarkable new talent Pascual Sisto&amp;#39;s feature debut offers an unsettling look at a kid with something missing where his conscience should be&amp;hellip; Like Dogtooth or Benny&amp;rsquo;s Video, it works as a kind of suburban surrealism&amp;hellip; With any luck, the film will put both Shotwell and Sisto on the map.&amp;rdquo; - Peter Debruge, Variety. &amp;nbsp;OFFICIAL SELECTION - 2020 CANNES FILM FESTIVAL and 2021 SUNDANCE FILM FESTIVAL. Directed by Pascual Sisto, one of Variety&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;10 Directors to Watch&amp;rdquo;; written by Nicol&amp;aacute;s Giacobone, OscarⓇ-winning co-writer of BIRDMAN, Co-writer of BIUTIFUL. Starring Charlie Shotwell (THE NEST), Michael C. Hall (Dexter), Jennifer Ehle (SAINT MAUD), Taissa Farmiga (American Horror Story.)&lt;/p&gt;

