Description: Once upon a time, in a small family suburb on the outskirts of Rome, the cheerful heat of summer camouflages a stifling atmosphere of alienation. &amp;nbsp;From a distance, the families seem normal, but it&amp;rsquo;s an illusion: in the houses, courtyards and gardens, silence shrouds the subtle sadism of the fathers, the passivity of the mothers and the guilty indifference of adults. &amp;nbsp;But it&amp;rsquo;s the desperation and repressed rage of the children that will explode and cut through this grotesque facade, with devastating consequences for the entire community. Directed by The D&amp;rsquo;Innocenzo Brothers (BOYS CRY, DOGMAN), BAD TALES stars Elio Germano, Barbara Chichiarelli, and Lino Musella.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I WAS A SIMPLE MAN-- Opening TBD;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3059279147680624&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=3059279147680624&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
A ghost story set in the pastoral countryside of the north shore of O&amp;#39;ahu, Hawai&amp;#39;i, incorporating familial history and mythology, dream logic and surrealism. &amp;nbsp;Revealed in four chapters, it tells the story of an elderly man facing the end of his life, visited by the ghosts of his past. Directed by Christopher Makoto Yogi, starring Constance Wu.&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;KENNY SCHARF: WHEN WORLDS COLLIDE&lt;br /&gt;
Launches in Theaters and Virtual Cinemas on Friday, June 25&lt;br /&gt;
More info at the film&amp;rsquo;s Greenwich website:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://greenwichentertainment.com/film/kenny-scharf-when-worlds-collide/&quot;&gt;https://greenwichentertainment.com/film/kenny-scharf-when-worlds-collide/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Trailer:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://bit.ly/KennyScharfTrailer&quot;&gt;http://bit.ly/KennyScharfTrailer&lt;/a&gt;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2951028218505718&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2951028218505718&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: A Vibrant Portrait of the LA-Based Pop Art Icon. Greenwich Entertainment is pleased to present KENNY SCHARF: WHEN WORLDS COLLIDE, a vibrant portrait of the life and work of the LA-based pop art icon and art world survivor. When you look at Kenny Scharf&amp;rsquo;s surreal, colorful, pop-culture inspired art you can&amp;rsquo;t help but wonder where he gets his inspiration. This documentary about Scharf&amp;rsquo;s fascinating life&amp;mdash;made over 11 years by the artist&amp;rsquo;s daughter, Malia Scharf, and Max Basch&amp;mdash;answers that question. Featuring interviews and rare archival footage with the artist himself along with Andy Warhol, Jean-Michel Basquiat, Keith Haring, Ed Ruscha, Dennis Hopper and Yoko Ono, the film shows Scharf&amp;rsquo;s arrival in New York City from Los Angeles in the early 1980s, where he quickly befriended Keith Haring and Jean Michel Basquiat. There, amongst the fervent creative bustle of a depressed downtown scene, the trio would soon take the art world by storm. But unlike Haring and Basquiat, who both died tragically young, Scharf lived through cataclysmic shifts in the East Village as well as the ravages of AIDS and economic depression. &amp;nbsp;Decades later, still obsessed with garbage, cartoons and plastic, and committed to the idea that art should be fun, Scharf&amp;rsquo;s whimsical mind continues to generate works rife with iconic images and bizarre forms. &amp;nbsp;WHEN WORLDS COLLIDE immerses us in the heart and soul of the times and the man who, despite setbacks along the way, perseveres in his living-life-out loud, technicolor artistic vision.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AMERICAN TRAITOR: THE TRIAL OF AXIS SALLY&lt;br /&gt;
Wednesday, May 26 at 7:30pm at the Laemmle Royal in West LA (11523 Santa Monica Blvd 1st floor, Los Angeles, CA 90025)&lt;br /&gt;
RSVP Tuesday, May 25th at Noon at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://click.icptrack.com/icp/relay.php?r=32993367&amp;amp;msgid=463633&amp;amp;act=HEZJ&amp;amp;c=800186&amp;amp;destination=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.laemmle.com%2Fsneak-preview%2Famerican-traitor-royal%3Futm_source%3DiContact%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Dsneak-announcement%26utm_content%3DCopy%2Bof%2BSneak%2B000%2B-%2BShiva%2BBaby%2B-%2BTown%2BCenter&amp;amp;cf=7493&amp;amp;v=d9d1bc76c67cfafadef3fee5ca6fab77425c50c72cd3d78f15a2d7b920c24639&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;this link here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: You are invited to a preview of Al Pacino&amp;#39;s new movie. Based on the true story, AMERICAN TRAITOR: THE TRIAL OF AXIS SALLY follows the life of American woman Mildred Gillars (Meadow Williams) and her lawyer (Al Pacino), who struggles to redeem her reputation. Dubbed &amp;ldquo;Axis Sally&amp;rdquo; for broadcasting Nazi propaganda to American troops during World War II, Mildred&amp;rsquo;s story exposes the dark underbelly of the Third Reich&amp;#39;s hate-filled propaganda machine, her eventual capture in Berlin, and subsequent trial for treason against the United States after the war. Co-starring Meadow Williams and Thomas Kretchmann and directed by Michael Polish.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AKILLA&amp;rsquo;S ESCAPE&lt;br /&gt;
Opens June 11, 2021 in select theaters and on digital platforms.&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3kZD5lCt4Q4&quot;&gt;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3kZD5lCt4Q4&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;;&amp;nbsp;Enjoy the KPFK Film Club Review here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=2942005369408003&amp;amp;id=1718261665115719&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://www.facebook.com/&lt;wbr /&gt;permalink.php?story_fbid=&lt;wbr /&gt;2942005369408003&amp;amp;id=&lt;wbr /&gt;1718261665115719&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: OFFICIAL SELECTION- TORONTO INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL/NOMINATED FOR SEVEN CANADIAN SCREEN AWARDS. In his latest feature, AKILLA&amp;rsquo;S ESCAPE, Charles Officer confronts toxic masculinity and shows how the actions of one man can halt the generational cycles of violence and poverty. Akilla, played masterfully by poet and actor Saul Williams, navigates the criminal underworld of Toronto and after a robbery gone awry, finds himself sucked back into the turbulent violence he has fought so long to escape. In two mirrored storylines, we watch Akilla as both a boy and a man resist this violent life and live by his own terms. A cinematic crime noir set to a soundtrack created by Saul Williams and Massive Attack&amp;rsquo;s 3D, AKILLA&amp;rsquo;S ESCAPE is a poignant art piece which presents an alternative definition to the media&amp;#39;s portrayal of Black masculinity. Written and directed by Charles Officer, starring and original score by Saul Williams. &amp;nbsp;A Vertical Entertainment Release. &amp;ldquo;A mature crime picture whose decades-hopping action makes the effects of generational poverty obvious without having to spell it out&amp;rdquo;- John DeFore, The Hollywood Reporter &amp;ldquo;There&amp;rsquo;s a really solid performance at the center from poet/musician Saul Williams&amp;rdquo; - Brian Tallerico, Roger Ebert. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Akilla&amp;rsquo;s Escape is a film about manhood, mercy, and second chances.&amp;rdquo;- Aramide Tinubu, Showbiz Cheat Sheet&lt;/p&gt;

