Description: This Yom HaShoah, we invite you to view the award-winning documentary. Narrated by Maya Angelou and co-produced by Sundance Channel. Directed by Hilary Helstein , USA, 2008. &amp;ldquo;I hope and pray you will be as inspired by these extraordinary people as I have been, I am now and shall forever be.&amp;rdquo; &amp;mdash; Maya Angelou. As Maya Angelou narrates this powerful documentary, she reveals the story of a brave group of people who fought Hitler with the only weapons they had: charcoal, pencil stubs, shreds of paper and memories etched in their minds. These artists took their fate into their own hands to make a compelling statement about the human spirit, enduring against unimaginable odds. Best Feature Documentary | Thessalonki Documentary Festival, Best Documentary | Los Angeles Jewish Film Festival, Best Documentary | Miami Jewish Film Festival, Best Documentary | Winnipeg International Film Festival, Best Documentary (Bronze Phoenix Award) | Warsaw International Festival of Jewish Motifs, Best Film | International Jewish Film Festival in Argentina&lt;/p&gt;

