Description: This Yom Hashoah, join the Los Angeles Jewish Film Festival, and their partner ChaiFlicks, as we remember and honor the millions of Jewish lives stolen in the Holocaust. They are proud to share their stories with powerful, award-winning films, streaming now on ChaiFlicks. The LAJFF invites you to view the award-winning documentary AS SEEN THROUGH THESE EYES. Narrated by Maya Angelou, this film reveals the story of a brave group of people who fought Hitler with the only weapons they had: charcoal, pencil stubs, shreds of paper and memories etched in their minds. They took their fate into their own hands to make a compelling statement about the human spirit, enduring against unimaginable odds. Includes an exclusive interview with Simon Wiesenthal and his never-before-seen artwork.&lt;/p&gt;

