Description: Winner of the World Cinema Jury Prize and a Nominee for the Grand Jury Prize ~ World Cinema Dramatic At the Sundance Film Festival! The late Mary Twala Mhlongo, recognizable from Beyonc&amp;eacute;&amp;rsquo;s blockbuster musical Black Is King, gives a heartbreaking career-capping performance as Mantoa, an 80-year-old woman who has lived in a small Lesotho village for her entire life. While preparing for her own death, she receives word of an accident that has killed her only son, leaving her entirely alone, with only the respect of her community, the traditions of her ancestors, and the courage of her convictions. When her community must relocate to make way for a nearby dam which would flood her family&amp;rsquo;s burial ground, Mantoa draws a line in the sand and becomes an unlikely political and spiritual leader. Berlin-based Mosotho filmmaker Lemohang Jeremiah Mosese&amp;rsquo;s devastating and hypnotic This Is Not a Burial, It&amp;rsquo;s a Resurrection is already one of the most esteemed African films ever to hit the international festival circuit, earning the Special Jury Prize for Visionary Filmmaking at the 2020 Sundance Film Festival, before taking home Best Actress, Best Director, and Best Cinematography at Africa&amp;rsquo;s Academy Awards. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;As classical in theme as it is adventurous in presentation.&amp;rdquo;-- Guy Lodge, Variety. Directed by Lemohang Jeremiah Mosese and starring Mary Twala and Jerry Mofokeng.&amp;nbsp;Mark your calendars&amp;hellip; Laemmle Theatres are reopening April 9th!&lt;/p&gt;

