Description: &amp;nbsp;A Special Yom Ha&amp;#39;Shoah Commemoration Event From the Los Angeles Jewish Film Fest. Join LAJFF in partnership with American Society for Yad Vashem, Holocaust Museum LA, Valley Beth Shalom and Chabad North of Montana for a special YOM HA&amp;rsquo;SHOAH EVENT. The award-winning, inspirational documentary, DETERMINED, follows Avraham Perlmutter as he outwits the Nazis and overcomes every obstacle standing in his way. But more than just a remarkable story of survival, his tale is a testament to human kindness, even in the darkest of hours, and to the achievements made possible through relentless perseverance. Q&amp;amp;A with filmmaker and Avraham&amp;rsquo;s daughter, writer/producer/director Dr. KEREN PERLMUTTER, the film&amp;rsquo;s composer STEVEN CHESNE, and the descendants of the BEIJERS FAMILY (who hid Avraham for over a year in the Netherlands and who were honored as &amp;ldquo;Righteous Among the Nations&amp;rdquo;), moderated by renowned Holocaust scholar, Dr. MICHAEL BERENBAUM. With this commemoration of Yom Ha&amp;#39;Shoah, the LAJFF will honor this local hero, Dr. Avraham Perlmutter, currently 93 years old, who is a long-time Los Angeles resident. PLEASE NOTE: Be sure to check your confirmation for pertinent info about the film and zoom. &amp;nbsp;An email with a link, password and instructions to watch the film will be sent to you before April 7th.&lt;/p&gt;

