Detailed information about local broadcasts nationwide are available here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theworldismycountry.com/publictv&quot;&gt;https://www.theworldismycountry.com/publictv&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Enjoy the trailer here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://vimeo.com/369956765&quot;&gt;https://vimeo.com/369956765&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Description: The World Is My Country, a new documentary film chronicling the life of the iconic &amp;quot;World Citizen #1&amp;quot; Garry Davis, will premiere on U.S. public television stations and PBS affiliates beginning in April, 2021. The film, introduced by Academy Award&amp;reg;-winning actor Martin Sheen, includes exclusive footage from Davis&amp;rsquo; live performances alongside pristine archival footage documenting his journey from Broadway actor to bomber pilot to being dubbed &amp;ldquo;World Citizen #1&amp;rdquo; by the media reports of the day. &amp;ldquo;Back in the Golden Age of Broadway Garry wowed audiences with his rapid-fire Danny Kaye number,&amp;rdquo; said director Arthur Kanegis, &amp;ldquo;but then he was drafted into World War II and ordered to bomb Brandenburg. Horrified at the carnage, he leapt off the Broadway stage onto the World stage &amp;mdash; taking on border guards, guns and jail &amp;ndash; in a jaw-dropping mission to unite the people of our world.&amp;rdquo; Davis&amp;rsquo; bold actions drew the support of Albert Einstein, Simone de Beauvoir, John Paul Sartre, Albert Camus and thousands more to a movement that culminated when the United Nations unanimously passed the Universal Declaration of Human Rights on Dec. 10,1948. For the next 65 years, Davis continued his effort to inspire &amp;ldquo;we the people&amp;rdquo; to take the lead in creating world law to outlaw war, oppression and the destruction of the environment &amp;mdash; and build a safe, secure and sustainable future for all. &amp;nbsp;In 2013 The New York Times titled his front-page obituary: &amp;ldquo;Man Of No Nation sees One World of No War.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Given the magnitude of today&amp;rsquo;s global challenges, from climate change and COVID-19 to displaced millions and nuclear war, the urgency of Garry&amp;rsquo;s ideas has never been greater&amp;rdquo; said Melanie Bennett, Producer of the film. &amp;ldquo;What drew me to this film is that Garry actually gives us a solution!&amp;rdquo; Albert Einstein was quoted as saying that Davis grasps the key to &amp;ldquo;whether mankind &amp;nbsp;will disappear by its own hand or continue to exist.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TELL MY STORY&lt;br /&gt;
