Description: SHORTLISTED FOR THE INTERNATIONAL FEATURE FILM CATEGORY FOR THE 93RD ACADEMY AWARDS, FROM BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA. Aida is a translator for the UN in the small town of Srebrenica. When the Serbian army takes over the town, her family is among the thousands of citizens looking for shelter in the UN camp. As an insider to the negotiations Aida has access to crucial information that she needs to interpret. What is on the horizon for her family and people - rescue or death? Which move should she take? &amp;ldquo;Powerful and personal&amp;rdquo;&amp;mdash;Mark Kermode, Observer. Winner, Best Film 2020&amp;mdash;Antalya Golden Orange Film Festival, Jerusalem Film Festival, Les Arcs European Film Festival; Best Film Nominee at the Venice Film Festival, Seville European Film Festival, Film Independent Spirit Awards&lt;/p&gt;

