&lt;b&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt; The Frida Cinema in Santa Ana presents Legendary Japanese director Takashi Miike&amp;rsquo;s 100th film, &amp;nbsp;the violent and strikingly beautiful BLADE OF THE IMMORTAL. Based on the Manga series &amp;ldquo;Mugen no j&amp;ucirc;nin&amp;rdquo; by Hiroaki Samura, Blade of the Immortal follows the deeds of Manji, a skilled samurai who has a decisive advantage: no wound can kill him.&amp;nbsp; He has taken a lot of lives, both innocent and guilty, and now lives life in feudal Japan as a criminal after being cursed with his immortality. His only possible salvation? He must honor his vow to kill enough evil men &amp;ndash; 1,000, to be exact &amp;ndash; before his curse is lifted and he can finally rest. When he comes across a young girl named Rin whose parents were killed by a group of master swordsmen led by ruthless warrior Anotsu, Manji makes an oath to help her avenge their deaths, leading the unlikely duo on a remarkable quest to make right against those who did them wrong. A kinetic and visually stunning ballet of violence, BLADE OF THE IMMORTAL combines fantastical and knowingly cartoonish elements with rich characterization, invested performances, and genuinely intense and gory battles, delivering a film that truly honors its page-tuner Manga roots while reveling in the sort of visual audacity and spectacle that only the art of cinema can offer. &amp;ldquo;Not often do you encounter a movie about slicing, dicing samurai vivisecting each other into gory chunks that is also a thing of beauty.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Colin Covert, Minneapolis Star Tribune &amp;ldquo;Further proof that of all the genres he dabbles in, samurai cinema is the one that brings out the grandest entertainer in Miike. Here&amp;rsquo;s to 100 more.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; A.A. Dowd, The AV Club &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Blade of the Immortal is flat-out gorgeous.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Gary Thompson, Philadelphia Inquirer &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Here&amp;rsquo;s to another 100!&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; James Berardinelli, ReelViews&lt;br /&gt;
