&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Another Fabulous Culture Vulture Event from the Amazing Laemmle Theaters--Titus Andronicus, Live from Stratford-Upon-Avon!!! When a society is oppressed, it becomes violent. How do we govern ourselves? In the chaos and disorder of 2017, Titus Andronicus is a commentary on the way this world could be going. Titus has returned from a brutal 10-year war having lost 21 sons in battle. Betrayed by his nation, and with his family in pieces, a series of bloody events follows as he and Tamora, Queen of the Goths begin a violent cycle of revenge. Rape, cannibalism, mutilation and murder are the gruesome tools in Shakespeare&amp;rsquo;s bloodiest play (the performance of Titus Andronicus has been issued an As Live 15 rating by the British Board of Film Classification for violent scenes.) Blanche McIntyre (The Two Noble Kinsmen, 2016) directs David Troughton in this chillingly contemporary Titus Andronicus. &amp;ldquo;A terrific cast give a masterclass in power and paranoia in a tremendous modern-day revival of Shakespeare&amp;rsquo;s tale of revenge.&amp;rdquo; --Michael Billington, Guardian&lt;br style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;
