gorical tale&amp;hellip;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;One of the best drama films of the latter half of the 20th century&amp;hellip; 1979&amp;rsquo;s Stalker is all that and more, relating the tale of 3 men traversing a forbidden&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border:0px; font-size:9pt; margin:0px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border:0px; font-size:9pt; margin:0px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:13.8px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;post-apocalyptic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Zone&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;to find a magical room which has the power to make wishes come true. Stalker is a metaphysical journey through a sentient heart of darkness, with unforgettable images and emotional intensity&amp;mdash;a rarely screened masterpiece which will grace the Frida&amp;rsquo;s screen Sept. 25, 26, and 30th.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;On the other side of the spectrum is the deliciously horrible 2003 film THE ROOM, sometimes called the &amp;ldquo;Citizen Kane of bad movies.&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;What THE ROOM is about is not nearly as important as the glee you&amp;rsquo;ll experience watching the most awesomely awful acting, writing, and all around ludicrous film-making since Ed Wood. This film sells out each and every time the Frida screens it, this time on September 29th!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/