le=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Two Gorgeous Films, Discussed by Award Winning Designers, Popcorn, Drinks, and More!! On Sunday, September 16, 10 Am to 5 PM, join the Frida Cinema for the first-ever 2017 OC Design Film Fest, presented by and benefiting the American Society of Interior Designers (ASID) - Orange County Chapter!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;You can enjoy TWO feature films - Steel Magnolias (starring Sally Field, Dolly Parton, Shirley MacLaine, Julia Roberts, Tom Skerritt, Sam Shepard, and more!), and Something&amp;#39;s Gotta Give (starring Jack Nicholson, Diane Keaton, Keanu Reeves, and Frances McDormand.)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;PLUS live speakers, popcorn and soft drink!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Or enjoy a &amp;quot;Dress Circle&amp;quot; ticket to get all this plus a Swag Bag and Catered Lunch! The organizers have lined up two incredibly special guests to join this unique event that takes a look at Interior Design in television and cinema: Beth Rubino&amp;mdash;An award-winning film production designer and set decorator, Beth is a two-time Academy Award nominee for Best Art Direction (The Cider House Rules, American Gangster), as well as an Emmy nominee for Best Production Design (&amp;quot;American Horror Story&amp;quot;). Her work on Something&amp;#39;s Gotta Give has become an inspiration for Kitchen Design world.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Melinda Ritz&amp;mdash;Award-winning set decorator and residential designer since 1985, Melinda started her 27-year career in film on such genre films as The Abyss and Basic Instinct. She went on to win three Emmy Awards, as well as seven nominations for her work on &amp;quot;Will &amp;amp; Grace&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Melinda has worked to develop and maximize the potential for gorgeous properties for such clients as Ellen DeGeneres, Ryan Seacrest, Kim and Kanye, and the famous Brody House.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Info and Advance tickets can be obtained at&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://remote.kpfk.org/owa/redir.aspx?SURL=EQfp7n3ENjl8vZla5B2Vln5NlU4y4ur6Nt0xPRF3l1jpPPURofzUCGgAdAB0AHAAOgAvAC8AbwBjAGQAZQBzAGkAZwBuAGYAaQBsAG0AZgBlAHMAdAAuAGUAdgBlAG4AdABiAHIAaQB0AGUALgBjAG8AbQA.&amp;amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2focdesignfilmfest.eventbrite.com&quot; style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:none; font-size:12px; background:transparent; text-decoration:none&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border:0px; font-size:9pt; margin:0px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration:none&quot;&gt;http://ocdesignfilmfest.&lt;wbr style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;eventbrite.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;border:0px; font-size:9pt; margin:0px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;!&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Proceeds benefit the American Society of Interior Designers (ASID) Orange County Chapter, dedicated to enriching professional relationships with all members while increasing membership, legislative, and public awareness of the Interior Design Field.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/s