le=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;An Utterly Original &amp;ndash; and Consistently, Endearingly Strange &amp;ndash; Independent Comedy at the MOST FABULOUS Frida Cinema in Santa Ana!!!Written by and starring comedian Kyle Mooney, Brigsby Bear has emerged as one of the most buzzed-about indies of the summer, and arrives at The Frida Cinema for one week, opening Friday August 25!!! &amp;ldquo;Brigsby Bear Adventures&amp;rdquo; is a quirky children&amp;rsquo;s TV show produced for an audience of one: isolated loner James Pope. When the show abruptly ends, James&amp;rsquo; sets out on a mission to finish the story himself &amp;ndash; leading him into a world full of alternately mesmerizing and terrifying realities he knows nothing about. &amp;ldquo;What a strange and lovely road we travel with Brigsby Bear.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;Richard Roeper, Chicago Sun-Times &amp;ldquo;A charming, surprisingly underplayed paean to pop-culture obsession.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; John DeFore, Hollywood Reporter &amp;ldquo;A sweet-natured picture with an undercurrent of prickly energy.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Stephanie Zacharek, TIME Magazine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

