&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Moka&amp;mdash;A moody, riveting psychological thriller, showcasing the tremendous talents of two of France&amp;rsquo;s best actresses.To find the driver of the vintage mocha-colored Mercedes which she thinks hit her son and devastated her life, Diane (Emmanuelle Devos) embarks on a trip to take revenge. She goes to &amp;Eacute;vian, where she has learned the driver of the Mercedes lives, but she now has to face another woman, Marlene (Nathalie Baye) &amp;ndash; a beauty salon proprietor and owner of the car. In order to get closer to her, Diane pretends to be a potential buyer for the car, but the path of revenge is more tortuous and complicated than it seems. &amp;nbsp;Adapted from Tatiana de Rosnay&amp;rsquo;s 2006 novel. &amp;ldquo;An elegantly lean, low-temperature thriller from Swiss writer-director Fr&amp;eacute;d&amp;eacute;ric Mermou.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash;Variety.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;A tense psychological thriller whose twisty plot benefits from a bravura performance by Emmanuelle Devos.&amp;rdquo; -LA Times.&amp;ldquo;You could rightly call it a thriller, but a slow-burning one, and a film that&amp;rsquo;s driven by character, not plot points.&amp;rdquo; -SF Chronicle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

