&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;MARK YOU CALENDERS&amp;mdash;YOU WON&amp;rsquo;T WANT TO MISS THIS ONE!!! THE QFILM FESTIVAL, Long Beach&amp;rsquo;s longest-running film festival since 1993, is coming September 7th-10th to the FABULOUS, beautifully renovated Art Theater in Long Beach!! The QFilm Festival annually presents narrative features, documentaries and short films that embody the richness and diversity of experiences of lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender and queer (LGBTQ) communities. More than 1,500 people attend each year to savor a mix of West Coast, Southern California and local premieres as well some of the most acclaimed features on the film festival circuit. 2017 highlights include opening night&amp;rsquo;s Long Beach premiere of The Untold Tales of Armistead Maupin (a new and acclaimed documentary about the longtime activist and author of the popular &amp;ldquo;Tales of the City&amp;rdquo; book series), THE FEELS (a hilarious, heartfelt award winning comedy), SOMETHING LIKE SUMMER (a romantic drama with musical interludes), four spectacular shorts programs, a special post QFilms performance of the Rocky Horror Picture Show with live shadow cast, and MUCH, MUCH, MORE!!!&amp;nbsp; Numerous filmmakers and cast members of the films will be present for audience discussions after each screening. Festival events will feature nightly parties, a fabulous Drag Queen&amp;nbsp;Sunday&amp;nbsp;Brunch at The LGBTQ Center of Long Beach, and opportunities for attendees to meet and mingle with filmmakers, actors, critics and other industry professionals. All net proceeds from the festival will benefit The LGBTQ Center of Long Beach and its important community outreach programs!!!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&g