&lt;p style=&quot;border:0px; margin:0px 0px 18px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-caps:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;orphans:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;widows:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;word-spacing:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-style:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-color:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;: Alejandro Jodorowsky, The Venerated Cult Cinema Master, at the Fabulous FRIDA CINEMA. There was once a time (1970&amp;rsquo;s) when you might saddle up to the counter of your small and struggling video store and plead with the bearded guy behind the counter to rent you his personal (probably bootleg) copy of El Topo.&amp;nbsp; It wasn&amp;rsquo;t like you hadn&amp;rsquo;t stood in line, more than once, for the midnight screening at the nearest art house cinema. &amp;nbsp;But the idea of watching this cult classic on your own TV, pausing and rewinding your way through the movie, seemed so&amp;hellip;.well, maybe spiritual isn&amp;rsquo;t quite the right word, but&amp;hellip;.Fast forward.&amp;nbsp; Now the REAL TREAT is sitting in the dark with like-minded Cinefiles and watching Jodorowsky&amp;rsquo;s cult masterpieces on the big screen,&amp;nbsp; where they truly belong. Well, again, the amazing Frida Cinema&amp;rsquo;s got you covered, screening Jodorowsky&amp;rsquo;s latest ode to the quest for beauty and inner truth, ENDLESS POETRY,&amp;nbsp; as well as a number of his classics, including EL TOPO (1970), THE HOLY MOUNTAIN (1973), and SANTA SANGRE (1990.)&amp;nbsp; You won&amp;rsquo;t want to miss them:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;border:0px; margin:0px 0px 18px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-caps:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;orphans:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;widows:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;word-spacing:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-style:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-color:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;ENDLESS POETRY&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;From the mind of visionary artist and filmmaker Alejandro Jodorowsky comes his latest sublime work of autobiography filtered through symbolism, Poesia sin fin (Endless Poetry).&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Endless Poetry&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;details Jodorowsky&amp;rsquo;s life from the time he left the Chilean coastal town of Tocopilla for Santiago at the age of nine, through his decision to move to France when he was in his 20s. The younger Alejandro is played by&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;The Dance of Reality&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Jodorowsky&amp;rsquo;s previous film) star Jeremias Herskovitz; Adan Jodorowsky, the director&amp;rsquo;s youngest son, who also composed the film&amp;rsquo;s score, plays the more mature Alejandro. Against the wishes of his authoritarian father (played by Brontis Jodorowsky, Alejandro&amp;rsquo;s oldest son) the 20-year-old protagonist leaves home to pursue his dream of becoming a poet, and is introduced to the bohemian and artistic inner circle of Santiago. He meets Enrique Lihn (Leandro Taub) and Stella Diaz (Pamela Flores), two unknown poets who would become driving forces of twentieth century Hispanic literature. Told through Jodorowsky&amp;rsquo;s unique surreal and psychedelic visual language,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Endless Poetry&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an ode to the quest for beauty and inner truth as a universal force capable of changing one&amp;rsquo;s life forever.&lt;br style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;
&amp;ldquo;The most accessible movie Jodorowsky has ever made, and it may also be his best. It&amp;rsquo;s Felliniesque and moving . . . Yet more than any previous Jodorowsky opus, it&amp;rsquo;s also a work of disciplined and touching emotional resonance.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Variety&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;border:0px; margin:0px 0px 18px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-caps:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;orphans:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;widows:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;word-spacing:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-style:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-color:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;El Topo&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;The genre of the Psychedelic Western launched in the late &amp;rsquo;60s, but its true form manifested itself in Alejandro Jodorowsky&amp;rsquo;s dreamlike, bizarre, and unforgettable epic&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;El Topo&lt;/em&gt;. A story about a mysterious gunfighter clad in black, this film pairs the mysticism of Eastern religions with extreme violence, enough to make Sam Peckinpah&amp;rsquo;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;The Wild Bunch&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;seem like a cartoon.&lt;br style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;
Originally released in 1970,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;El Topo&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;quickly caught the imagination of movie audiences, becoming a landmark in independent film-making. The early screenings at New York&amp;rsquo;s Elgin Theater sparked the Midnight Movie phenomena, catalyzed by an endorsement from John Lennon and Yoko Ono. Classic Americana and avant-garde European sensibilities collide with Zen Buddhism and the Bible as master gunfighter and mystic El Topo (played by Jodorowsky himself) tries to defeat four sharp-shooting rivals on a bizarre path to allegorical self-awareness and resurrection. As it seeks an alternative to the Hollywood mainstream,&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;El Topo&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;is also the most controversial quasi-Western head trip ever made!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;border:0px; margin:0px 0px 18px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-caps:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;orphans:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;widows:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;word-spacing:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-style:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-color:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;The Holy Mountain&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;Need a religious experience? How about an acid trip? Why not both? The scandal of the 1973 Cannes Film Festival, Alejandro Jodorowsy&amp;rsquo;s seminal hallucinogenic work&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;The Holy Mountain&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;takes every religion, throws them in a mixer, and makes a hell of a cocktail.&amp;nbsp; Focused on a thief/Christ-like drifter, the narrative hopscotches around to different drug-induced reenactments of history, including the conquest of Mexico fought between iguanas and frogs&amp;mdash;and that&amp;rsquo;s just the beginning. From there he meets an alchemist (played by Jodorowsky himself), who takes him and seven figures to the titular Holy Mountain for the craziest enlightenment of all time. Equally appalling and hilarious,&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;The Holy Mountain&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;is one of the greatest cult classics of the 1970s.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;border:0px; margin:0px 0px 18px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-style:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-ligatures:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-caps:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight:400&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;orphans:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-transform:none&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;white-space:normal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;widows:2&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;word-spacing:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-style:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration-color:initial&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;SANTA SANGRE&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;Director Alejandro Jodorowsky is at his surreal best with this off-the-wall shocker from the late &amp;rsquo;80s.&amp;nbsp; A traumatized young boy spends his life in a mental institution, only to rejoins his mother, former leader of the heretical&amp;nbsp;&lt;em style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Santa Sangre&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;(&amp;ldquo;Holy Blood&amp;rdquo;) church, whose arms were cut off by his philandering circus-performer father. As all mother-son relationships in horror go, mother knows best&amp;hellip;, and with her son by her side, she sets out an exacting revenge against all who have wronged her, and who pose a threat to her renewed family unit.&lt;br style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;
