&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;The fascinating documentary The CHINESE LIVES OF ULI SIGG portrays Uli Sigg&amp;#39;s involvement in China&amp;rsquo;s recent opening to the West, and of the West&amp;rsquo;s embrace of Chinese contemporary art, through the eyes of Sigg and the artists he championed. &amp;nbsp;Uli Sigg is a Swiss businessman, diplomat and art collector who served as the Swiss Ambassador to China, North Korea and Mongolia.&amp;nbsp; In 2012 he made a large donation of contemporary Chinese art to the Hong Kong-based M+ museum in 2012.&amp;nbsp; In 2019, the M+ museum for visual culture in Hong Kong will present 1500 art works by contemporary Chinese Artist to the public. The collection is credited the most important of its kind worldwide. &amp;quot;Required viewing for contemporary-art fans. Here&amp;rsquo;s a definitive portrait not just of the soft-spoken collector who brought the likes of Ai Weiwei and Cao Fei to the world&amp;rsquo;s attention but of the birthing pains of post-Mao China.&amp;rdquo; &amp;mdash;The Georgia Straight.&amp;nbsp; &amp;quot;A surprising film! [Uses] the impenetrable Uli Sigg to show us the hidden side of a complex and mysterious country... An intimate yet delicately icy portrait of a character who nurtures mystery like a defense weapon.&amp;rdquo; &amp;mdash;Cineuropa&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

