&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;One of the MOST ANTICIPATED SUMMER EVENTS is almost upon us!! On July 21st&amp;nbsp; the amazing Art Theater in Long Beach begins its screening of DUNKIRK, the World War II thriller starring Tom Hardy, Kenneth Branagh, and Mark Rylance. In May 1940, Germany advanced into France, trapping Allied troops on the beaches of Dunkirk. Under air and ground cover from British and French forces, troops were slowly and methodically evacuated from the beach using every serviceable naval and civilian vessel that could be found. At the end of this heroic mission, 330,000 French, British, Belgian and Dutch soldiers were safely evacuated. Acclaimed auteur Christopher Nolan (INSOMNIA, THE DARK KNIGHT TRILOGY, INTERSTELLER) directs, telling this thrilling story from three perspectives&amp;ndash;the land, sea and air&amp;ndash;with filming taking place on location in Dunkirk, France.&amp;nbsp; More than 6,000 extras were employed, as well as boats that had participated in the real Dunkirk evacuation and genuine era-appropriate planes for aerial sequences. The beautifully renovated Art Theater in Long Beach is the perfect place to see this cinematic event.&lt;br style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;
