&lt;b style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Fathom Events brings you James Levine conducting the legendary Placido Domingo LIVE from the MET!! Verdi&amp;rsquo;s third opera, NABUCCO, is a stirring drama about the fall of ancient Jerusalem at the hands of Nebuchadnezzar.&amp;nbsp; Nabucco catapulted the then 28-year-old composer to international fame. The music and Verdi himself were subsumed into a surge of patriotic fervor culminating in the foundation of the modern nation of Italy. The Chorus of the Hebrew Slaves (&amp;ldquo;Va, pensiero&amp;rdquo;), in which the Israelites express their longing for their homeland, has become an encore in many opera houses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

