t;border:0px; font-size:9pt; margin:0px; padding:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background:transparent&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;outline:0px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height:13.8px&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:black&quot;&gt;Expand your mind and un-tether your spirit!! Trisha Brown revolutionized the world of contemporary dance with her post-modern creations. &amp;quot;The grande dame, the high priestess&amp;mdash;in the world of postmodern dance, Brown stands apart,&amp;quot; wrote&amp;nbsp;The New Yorker of the ground-breaking choreographer. Now, the National Paris Opera Ballet is staging Brown&amp;#39;s seminal 1979 work&amp;nbsp;Glacial Decoy, with costumes and projected slides by the similarly risk-taking artist Robert Rauschenberg, performed by a new generation of dancers. The documentary film&amp;nbsp;In the Steps of Trisha Brown&amp;nbsp;follows the process of the young dancers learning the piece from Lisa Kraus and Carolyn Lucas, Trisha Brown&amp;#39;s collaborators, while telling the story of the evolution and development of Brown&amp;#39;s dance practice. Culminating in the staging of&amp;nbsp;Glacial Decoy, the film is a privileged look at the process of staging a major dance piece and a testament to the value of teaching and studying art. &amp;quot;Some of us only dream about flying; Trisha Brown launches her dreams onto the stage.&amp;rdquo; &amp;mdash;The Village Voice&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

