&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;DESCRIPTION&lt;/strong&gt;: LA FORZA DEL DESTINO, by master Giuseppe Verdi, is an wonderful opera in 4 acts.&amp;nbsp; La forza del destino&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; what is the meaning of the destiny that Verdi uses so forcefully? Who forces Leonora, and Alvaro as the murderer of her father, to enter the hermitage of a monastery &amp;ndash; and confronts them there, in a mighty showdown, with the brother who is full of hatred and cannot forgive? Is it a declaration of war against God&amp;rsquo;s promise of redemption? The heavenly cantilena of a solo violin rises at the end of the opera &amp;ndash; in the face of the death of the hero&amp;rsquo;s lover and brother. Those who withdraw into the consoling twilight of a divine peace here are only trying to deny one thing: the force of destiny.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

