Info from Fathom Events here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.fathomevents.com/events/der-rosenkavalier&quot; style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:none; font-size:12px; background:transparent; text-decoration:none&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.fathomevents.com/events/der-rosenkavalier&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px&quot; /&gt;
&lt;strong style=&quot;margin:0px; padding:0px; border:0px; outline:0px; font-size:12px; background:transparent&quot;&gt;DESCRIPTION:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Der Rosenkavalier--The magnificent music of Richard Strauss and a Farewell Performance by the Legendary Ren&amp;eacute;e Fleming! Fathom Events and The MET, Live in HD, present Ren&amp;eacute;e Fleming as she retires one of her best signature roles&amp;mdash; Strauss&amp;rsquo;s Marschallin, an attractive, worldly-wise princess in 18th-century Vienna. Strauss&amp;rsquo;s most popular opera concerns a wise woman of the world who is involved with a much younger lover, and who ultimately gives him up to a pretty young heiress. The story deftly combines comedy, dreamy nostalgic fantasy, genuine human drama, and light but striking touches of philosophy and social commentary. And the magnificent score combines the refinement of Mozart with the epic grandeur of Wagner. Fleming stars opposite Elīna Garanča in her first North American performances as Octavian, the impulsive young title character. The cast also includes G&amp;uuml;nther Groissb&amp;ouml;ck as Baron Ochs, Erin Morley as Sophie, Marcus Br&amp;uuml;ck in his Met debut as Faninal, and Matthew Polenzani as the Italian Singer. Conducted by Sebastian Weigle and directed by Robert Carsen, who most recent Met production was the hit 2013 staging of Falstaff, Der Rosenkavalier is a co-production with the Royal Opera House, Covent Garden, and Teatro Regio di Torino. Go behind the scenes with the Met&amp;#39;s stars! During intermission, interviews with cast, crew, and production teams give a revealing look at what goes into the staging of an opera.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

