&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing:inherit; font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: BROTHERS OF THE WIND&amp;mdash;A Heartwarming Story Breathtakingly Filmed!! Jean Reno (Leon: The Professional) stars alongside Manuel Camacho in Brothers of the Wind, an inspiring new Austrian release, and winner of Austria&amp;rsquo;s Romy Gala Award for Best Cinematography. &amp;nbsp;When 14-year old Lukas (Camacho) encounters a wounded baby eagle, they embark on a magical adventure filled with friendship, love, and hope. Having fallen from its mother&amp;rsquo;s nest, the baby eagle &amp;ndash; who Lukas has named Abel -depends on Lukas to nurture him; but as their friendship develops, so does the pressure to move on and find their own fates. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;A film with virtuoso images of fine falconry, as the narrator underlines the myth of Cain and Abel through the friendship of a child and a wild animal.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Carlos Mara&amp;ntilde;&amp;oacute;n Cineman&amp;iacute;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

