&lt;b style=&quot;box-sizing:inherit; font-weight:bold&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;: Director Travis Knight&amp;rsquo;s breathtaking 2016 stop-motion animation masterpiece KUBO AND THE TWO STRINGS comes to The Frida Cinema! Nominated for Academy Awards for Best Animated Feature Film and Best Visual Effects, and winner of the BAFTA for Best Animated Feature Film. From acclaimed animation studio LAIKA comes the story of Kubo, a young boy who lives a quaint, standard life in a small oceanside village. When he accidentally summons a spirit from his past which storms down from the heavens to avenge a historic grudge, Kubo finds himself on the run with Monkey (voiced by Charlize Theron) and Beetle (voiced by Matthew McConaughey), off on a riveting quest to find his late father&amp;rsquo;s mystical suit of armour &amp;mdash; the only thing that can defeat the spirit and rescue his family. &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Kubo is bold and daring, telling a truly unique tale set in ancient Japan that is rich with the depth of a story passed down for generations.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; Adam Graham, Detroit News; &amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Filmgoers who&amp;rsquo;ve suffered through a summer of superheroes, supervillains and sequels/snarky reboots: we now have something that genuinely casts a spell on viewers.&amp;rdquo; &amp;ndash; David Fear, &amp;nbsp;Rolling Stone&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

